issue_title: Welcome screen on every editor window is very tedious
issue_body:
I just discovered Gitlens and find the functionality useful, thank you to all who contribute.

I have about a dozen editor windows open, and the install process added a Gitlens welcome tab to each and every one of them.  Combined with the snowflake effect, all of the sudden VScode was consuming 300-400% cpu and my fan was raging, as soon as I hunted them all down everything was back to fine.  The welcome note content is great (although putting it on _all_ the windows is a bit much, don't know how much control you have on that).  But overall it was a bit of a sour first-use experience, just wanted to provide that feedback.

AutoObsidian tool handling: Use Silktouch pick for digging, use Fortune pick for echests
issue_body:
**Purpose:** if players are low on picks and want to use them as efficient as possible it is necessary to use fortune picks for echests and all other picks (i.e. silktouch or unenchanted diamond) for digging. This is a problem if the tunnel is not pre-dug since this uses lots of durability of the precious fortune pick.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Setting for proper use of picks. if turned on, autoobsidian prefers fortune picks and digging netherrack prefers  the best picks first (first enchanted, then unenchanted diamond). Also, ItemSaver in InventoryManager can be turned on so that the last fortune pick will not be used and can be mended (with xp bottles or by using mining quartz).

issue_title: make it so labels can have multiple characters
issue_body:
currently the `labelset` specified in a config.toml file gets converted to a (Python) `set` of single-character strings

this prevents a user from working with annotations where some segments have multi-character strings

conversion is done by `vak.config.converters.labelset_from_toml_value` function.
should maintain function's current behavior for strings, but change behavior for lists in the following way:
- [ ] any multi-character element in a list that is **not** a  "rangestr" stays as is. "rangestr" gets converted as before by passing it through
- [ ] do **not** require list to be all strings or all ints.  This leaves open possibility to fail silently currently (because the converter function just returns a `None` right now if the list is not all ints or all strs).
- [ ] simply cast ints to string, convert any "rangestr", and leave anything else (single/multi-character string) untouched

issue_title: unhandledRejection on remote import without body
issue_body:
Hello.

Since the switch from `requests` to `native-request` UrlFileManager does not handle redericts anymore. This leads to an error [here](https://github.com/less/less.js/blob/master/packages/less/src/less/import-manager.js#L82) (and possibly in other similar code) if response body is empty (like often happens with 301 responses). The error is

```
Warning: Empty body (HTTP 301) returned by "https://url.that/redirects/here"

.../node_modules/less/lib/less/import-manager.js:97
                var contents = loadedFile.contents.replace(/^\uFEFF/, '');
                                                   ^

TypeError: Cannot read property 'replace' of null
    at loadFileCallback (.../node_modules/less/lib/less/import-manager.js:97:52)
```

Which might be fine when you use less from CLI. But the real issue happens when you try to call `less.parse` directly in your code. Somehow instead of passing the error to a callback, or rejecting a promise `less.parse` causes `unhandledRejection`.

issue_title: derive Copy for ID
issue_body:
First of all Happy New Year to repo maintainers! Thank you for creating such easy to use library. Wish you all a great new year!

I am writing quite a bit of tests and need to pass `ID` around across different queries, I wonder if any technical reasons we don't have `derive Copy for ID` ? Currently I have to `id.to_string()` then `ID(string)`  back.

issue_title: Context menu - add a button to access the context menu, as well as right click (or add to Options menu) to
issue_body:
To me, a UWP program should not use "right click" Do others?
It is awkward on a touch screen/logical keyboard.
I get that the desktop version does, and have no problem with right click remaining. I just feel the options should be available by either the options menu or a button.

Add a button near the + ("create new item" button (navigation line), to get the menu?

On the same concept, could also add a dedicated properties button too.

issue_title: Profile page
issue_body:
There is already a component which allows updating the profile when a user is filling a form for an event. 

- Create an edit profile page using that component
- Create a profile page which is publicly visible

issue_title: Sliding scale for model acceptance threshold
issue_body:
[Requested from uninstall Typeform]
"It would have been perfect if I could have turned off the intent validation. Frankly, the model just isn't good enough to determine whether my intent is productive or not. I really just wanted to use the extension to prove to myself that I actually had a reason for going to certain websites."

- Setting in "options" page that allows user to vary acceptance threshold (adjusting the leniency of the prompt page)

issue_title: [Bug] Permanent drop in FPS due to emmVRC's Favorite Avatars row.
issue_body:
emmVRC Favorite List continues to render even though the menu has been closed. This generates a large permanent FPS loss depending on the favorite avatars you have.
For example, I have 113 favorite avatars and I lose between 20 and 30 fps on Desktop. (114 fps to 80)

When you start VRChat, the game runs at its maximum FPS. But when you open the Avatars menu this problem occurs and it affects even if you close the menu.

In emmVRC> Settings we can Disable emmVRC Favorite List, this returns our FPS, but if we activate it they go back down.

Solution: Stop rendering this row of favorite avatars when the VRChat menu remains closed.

issue_title: Solution 6 - minimal web api as a client.
issue_body:
Extend solution 5 by replacing the console client with a minimal web api client (basically the weather api but simplified to one "hello world" controller, no authentication or HTTPS.

What I would like to demonstrate with solution 6 is:

* obviously how to call the cluster from a web api
* cancellation tokens - web api controllers have built-in cancellation tokens in their actions (see here: https://eateam.visualstudio.com/Emailage%20Code/_git/greetings-planet?path=%2Fapi%2FControllers%2FHelloWorld.cs&version=GBmain) + grain cancellation tokens (https://dotnet.github.io/orleans/docs/grains/cancellation_tokens.html)
* ideally a pool of `ClusterClientHostedService` in every api so that api throughput is not bottle-necked by having only one `ClusterClientHostedService` per api host.

issue_title: Getting Started with GitHub
issue_body:
# :wave: Welcome to GitHub Learning Lab's "Introduction to GitHub" To get started, I’ll guide you through some important first steps in coding and collaborating on GitHub. :point_down: _This arrow means you can expand the window! Click on them throughout the course to find more information._
What is GitHub?
## What is GitHub? I'm glad you asked! Many people come to GitHub because they want to contribute to open source [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#open-source) projects, or they're invited by teammates or classmates who use it for their projects. Why do people use GitHub for these projects? **At its heart, GitHub is a collaboration platform.** From software to legal documents, you can count on GitHub to help you do your best work with the collaboration and security tools your team needs. With GitHub, you can keep projects completely private, invite the world to collaborate, and streamline every step of your project. **GitHub is also a powerful version control tool.** GitHub uses Git [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#git), the most popular open source version control software, to track every contribution and contributor [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#contributor) to your project--so you know exactly where every line of code came from. **GitHub helps people do much more.** GitHub is used to build some of the most advanced technologies in the world. Whether you're visualizing data or building a new game, there's a whole community and set of tools on GitHub that can get you to the next step. This course starts with the basics, but we'll dig into the rest later! :tv: [Video: What is GitHub?](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w3jLJU7DT5E)

Exploring a GitHub repository
## Exploring a GitHub repository :tv: [Video: Exploring a repository](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R8OAwrcMlRw) ### More features The video covered some of the most commonly-used features. Here are a few other items you can find in GitHub repositories: - Project boards: Create Kanban-style task tracking board within GitHub - Wiki: Create and store relevant project documentation - Insights: View a drop-down menu that contains links to analytics tools for your repository including: - Pulse: Find information about the work that has been completed and the work that’s in-progress in this project dashboard - Graphs: Graphs provide a more granular view of the repository activity including who contributed to the repository, who forked it, and when they completed the work ### Special Files In the video you learned about a special file called the README.md. Here are a few other special files you can add to your repositories: - CONTRIBUTING.md: The `CONTRIBUTING.md` is used to describe the process for contributing to the repository. A link to the `CONTRIBUTING.md` file is shown anytime someone creates a new issue or pull request. - ISSUE_TEMPLATE.md: The `ISSUE_TEMPLATE.md` is another file you can use to pre-populate the body of an issue. For example, if you always need the same types of information for bug reports, include it in the issue template, and every new issue will be opened with your recommended starter text.
### Using issues This is an issue [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#issue): a place where you can have conversations about bugs in your code, code review, and just about anything else. Issue titles are like email subject lines. They tell your collaborators what the issue is about at a glance. For example, the title of this issue is Getting Started with GitHub.
Using GitHub Issues ## Using GitHub issues Issues are used to discuss ideas, enhancements, tasks, and bugs. They make collaboration easier by: - Providing everyone (even future team members) with the complete story in one place - Allowing you to cross-link to other issues and pull requests [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#pull-request) - Creating a single, comprehensive record of how and why you made certain decisions - Allowing you to easily pull the right people and teams into a conversation with @-mentions :tv: [Video: Using issues](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zhj46r5D0nQ)
Managing notifications
## Managing notifications :tv: [Video: Watching, notifications, stars, and explore](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ocQldxF7fMY) Once you've commented on an issue or pull request, you'll start receiving email notifications when there's activity in the thread. ### How to silence or unmute specific conversations 1. Go to the issue or pull request 2. Under _"Notifications"_, click the **Unsubscribe** button on the right to silence notifications or **Subscribe** to unmute them You'll see a short description that explains your current notification status. ### How to customize notifications in Settings 1. Click your profile icon 2. Click **Settings** 3. Click **Notifications** from the menu on the left and [adjust your notification preferences](https://help.github.com/articles/managing-notification-delivery-methods/) ### Repository notification options * **Watch**: You'll receive a notification when a new issue, pull request or comment is posted, and when an issue is closed or a pull request is merged * **Not watching**: You'll no longer receive notifications unless you're @-mentioned * **Ignore**: You'll no longer receive any notifications from the repository ### How to review notifications for the repositories you're watching 1. Click your profile icon 2. Click **Settings** 3. Click **Notification** from the menu on the left 4. Click on the [things you’re watching](https://github.com/watching) link 5. Select the **Watching** tab 6. Click the **Unwatch** button to disable notifications, or **Watch** to enable them

Keep reading below to find your first task

issue_title: gradle does not provide modules/*.jar for transient dependencies (regression)
issue_body:
### What you were trying to do

Get a module's sources for development and play testing.

### What actually happened

Got module's sources, built module, but the game was not able to resolve the module's dependencies in the Advanced Game Setup screen.

### How to reproduce

* start with empty `modules/` workspace
* groovyw module get JoshariasSurvival
* gradlew jar
* gradlew game
* create new game, advanced setup, observe JoshariasSurvival is lacking its transient dependencies

### Log details and game version

I'm not actually watching this error happen right now, this report is assembled from Niruandaleth's notes and my understanding of gradle.


### Discussion

I expect this started when Core Upheaval removed transient dependencies from many module.txt at around the same time as the Gradle 6.4 branch made some adjustments to how it treats compile-time dependencies.

The thing that makes the `.jar` files show up in the `modules/` directory when a module is built from source is the `RemoteModuleGatherer` we have in our gradle configuration.

The crux of the issue is here:

https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/blob/957543938f28d703e3175e0ca6f2c5f64da0dd1d/build.gradle#L262

it's only checking the compile-time classpath, which don't include the transient dependencies.

Changing that to include the run-time classpath is a small change. However, I'm not fully confident that the PC facade knows it needs to resolve the runtime classpath of the modules before it starts. If it doesn't, there will be nothing for the RemoteModuleGatherer to observe and copy.

issue_title: Remove "Forum thread:"
issue_body: The forum thread link element adds "forum thread: " to any link you create using [forum=n,m]text[/forum].  That makes it awkward to make inline links. issue_title: Insufficient Type Constraint for Records
The schemagen tool and graphqlservice library should be aware of the version at runtime
issue_body:
Currently there's a `version.txt` file which is only used to determine the project version in CMake, and it's kept in synch with the latest release tag. There are several places where it would make sense to integrate that into the binaries as well:

- [x] The `schemagen` tool should implement a `--version` flag which reports the release it was built from.
- [x] Generated files should include the version they were built against and report an error/warning if used with an incompatible `graphqlservice` library at compile time, indicating that they should be regenerated. At runtime they might throw an exception.
- [x] On Windows, all of the binaries (exe and dll) should have a version number stamp in the file metadata.

issue_title: Enable admins to rename a system component (e.g., element)
issue_body:
**Story:**

As a GovReady administrator, 
I want an edit button near the name of a component in the Component Library pages,
so that I can update the name of a component.

**Acceptance criteria:**

GIVEN I have GovReady admin privileges,
WHEN I am on the component detail page for a component in the component library,
THEN I see an edit button to update the name of a component.

GIVEN I have GovReady admin privileges,
and GIVEN I am on the component detail page for a component in the component library,
and GIVEN I see an edit button to update the name of a component,
WHEN I click the component name edit button,
THEN I see simple pop-up to rename the component (or cancel) the action.

GIVEN I have GovReady admin privileges,
and GIVEN I have clicked the component name edit button,
WHEN I enter a new name and save the change,
THEN the name of the component is changed in the database,
AND the name change is logged using the existing logger infrastructure,
AND the name updates on the web page I am viewing.

A very simple initial unit test is written to updating the name of a component.

A very simple initial UI test is written to test the existence of the button on the component page if the user is an admin.

issue_title: Discrepancy between build.cmd and IDE build
issue_body:
When I type build.cmd to build the MSBuild repo on Windows it ends up with this command line:

```
/m /nologo /clp:Summary /v:minimal /nr:True /p:ContinuousIntegrationBuild=False /warnaserror /p:TreatWarningsAsErrors=true "C:\Users\kirill\.nuget\packages\microsoft.dotnet.arcade.sdk\1.0.0-beta.20580.3\tools\Build.proj" "/bl:C:\msbuild\artifacts\log\Debug\Build.binlog" "/p:Configuration=Debug" "/p:RepoRoot=C:\msbuild" "/p:Restore=True" "/p:DeployDeps=False" "/p:Build=True" "/p:Rebuild=False" "/p:Deploy=False" "/p:Test=False" "/p:Pack=False" "/p:IntegrationTest=False" "/p:PerformanceTest=False" "/p:Sign=False" "/p:Publish=False""
```

When I open MSBuild.Dev.sln in Visual Studio, some of these properties are not set, so the in-IDE behavior is slightly different. Specifically, projects always rebuild even if nothing has changed: this file: `C:\msbuild\artifacts\obj\Microsoft.Build.Framework\Debug\net472\Microsoft.Build.Framework.AssemblyInfo.cs` has an extra attribute (`[assembly: System.Reflection.AssemblyMetadataAttribute("RepositoryUrl", "https://github.com/microsoft/msbuild")]`) compared to the command-line build. It gets added because of a different default (`GenerateRepositoryUrlAttribute = true` in the IDE builds).

I think the default behavior for build.cmd should match as closely as possible the defaults picked by the build if you just do `msbuild /r /m /bl` with no extra properties. This way opening the solution in the IDE will result in the same builds instead of flip-flopping and competing with the command-line build and breaking incrementality.

issue_title: Create function to call if the RTOS fails
issue_body: Right now, if an os function returns an error, we are posting the fault state semaphore to go into a fault condition. This could be an issue if whatever causes the os function to fail causes the scheduler to not properly schedule the fault state task to run. One way to fix this would be to write a fault function that does the entire shutdown sequence and call it from the `assertOSError()` function. We can also call this function whenever we enter a fault state through the fault state thread, or if we reach the hard fault handler.

issue_body: We should write a hard fault handler, so if the BPS hard faults, we will enter a fault condition instead of using the default handler (infinite while loop)

Hi,

we are currently migrating our whole infrastructure and services from rancher 1.x to rancher 2.x. At the beginning we felt in love with longhorn.
Unfortunately volumes are stuck in degraded mode or become read-only. If the read-only issue happens some services (for instance gitlab postgres) crashs and we have to restart the workload manually.

issue_title: Change icon CSS classes to fill attribute
issue_body:
Hello all,
I've been using SVG icons in my portfolio and I encountered a problem with inconsistency of color filling. Most of the icons are properly styled with `fill` attribute but some of them use CSS classes `.cls-1`, `.cls-2` and so on. It creates a scope problem and each next icon using CSS classes overdrives color of the previous ones.


**A bad example (npm icon)**

```html
      <svg viewBox="0 0 128 128">
        <defs>
          <style>
            .cls-1 {
              fill: #cb3837;
            }
          </style>
        </defs>
        <title>Artboard 5</title>
        <path
          id="original-wordmark"
          class="cls-1"
          d="M2,38.5H126V82.21H64V89.5H36.44V82.21H2ZM8.89,74.93H22.67V53.07h6.89V74.93h6.89V45.79H8.89ZM43.33,45.79V82.21H57.11V74.93H70.89V45.79Zm13.78,7.29H64V67.64H57.11Zm20.67-7.29V74.93H91.56V53.07h6.89V74.93h6.89V53.07h6.89V74.93h6.89V45.79Z"
        ></path>
      </svg>
```

**After improvement (npm icon)**

```html
      <svg role="img" viewBox="0 0 128 128">
        <path
          fill="#cb3837"
          d="M2,38.5H126V82.21H64V89.5H36.44V82.21H2ZM8.89,74.93H22.67V53.07h6.89V74.93h6.89V45.79H8.89ZM43.33,45.79V82.21H57.11V74.93H70.89V45.79Zm13.78,7.29H64V67.64H57.11Zm20.67-7.29V74.93H91.56V53.07h6.89V74.93h6.89V53.07h6.89V74.93h6.89V45.79Z"
        ></path>
      </svg>
```

**My solution**
- check all SVG icons one by one
- remove all of CSS Classes
- use `fill` attribute for color
- remove `title` attribute or change to matching one (optional)

I would be happy to fix that issue if there's a need for that.

issue_title: Add more nav buttons on home page
Not saving WSJT-X QSOs
issue_body:
Right now, Kellog is not saving logged QSOs sent by kel-agent.

Turns out, that's because kel-agent is serializing multiple JSON documents in a single websocket message:

```
{"version":"kel-agent v0.2.2 (f03f44e)","wsjtx":{"type":"QsoLoggedMessage","payload":{"id":"WSJT-X","dateTimeOff":"2021-01-03T00:43:45Z","dxCall":"K6ESE","dxGrid":"EL09","txFrequency":7076100,"mode":"FT8","reportSent":"-15","reportReceived":"-07","txPower":"100","comments":"","name":"","dateTimeOn":"2021-01-03T00:42:45Z","operatorCall":"","myCall":"K0SWE","myGrid":"DM79LV","exchangeSent":"","exchangeReceived":""}}}
{"version":"kel-agent v0.2.2 (f03f44e)","wsjtx":{"type":"LoggedAdifMessage","payload":{"id":"WSJT-X","adif":"\n\u003cadif_ver:5\u003e3.1.0\n\u003cprogramid:6\u003eWSJT-X\n\u003cEOH\u003e\n\u003ccall:5\u003eK6ESE \u003cgridsquare:4\u003eEL09 \u003cmode:3\u003eFT8 \u003crst_sent:3\u003e-15 \u003crst_rcvd:3\u003e-07 \u003cqso_date:8\u003e20210103 \u003ctime_on:6\u003e004245 \u003cqso_date_off:8\u003e20210103 \u003ctime_off:6\u003e004345 \u003cband:3\u003e40m \u003cfreq:8\u003e7.076100 \u003cstation_callsign:5\u003eK0SWE \u003cmy_gridsquare:6\u003eDM79LV \u003ctx_pwr:3\u003e100 \u003cEOR\u003e"}}}
```

```
SyntaxError: Unexpected token { in JSON at position 419
    at JSON.parse (<anonymous>)
    ...
```

The correct behavior is probably for kel-agent to send only one JSON document per websocket message. As a workaround, Kellog can split on line separators.

issue_title: fallin' demo breaks when run atop sexblitter-drawn background on glibc 2.31
issue_body:
This requires:

* running a terminal which uses sexblitter (VTE, Kitty),
* running `fallin'` following a demo which uses a sextant background (`luigi` works),  and
* a libc lacking Unicode 13 support (e.g. Debian Unstable's 2.31)

`fallin'` reads the background character (a sextant), then tries to put it through `cell_prime()`. This fails, because older `wcwidth()` returns -1 for Unicode 13 characters (we work around this in the sexblitter via direct blitting, which isn't exposed beyond the library core).

This doesn't happen with the actual Debian/Fedora release, because `luigi` is disabled in DFSG builds. But check out head, build it locally, and run the default demo, and it'll happen.

issue_title: Logback should not be a runtime transitive dependency
issue_body:
As noted in the[ SLF4J documentation](http://www.slf4j.org/manual.html#libraries), libraries should not impose a logging framework on their end-users:

> Basic rule: Embedded components such as libraries or frameworks should not declare a dependency on any SLF4J binding but only depend on slf4j-api.

 This is so that the end-user can either choose the desired logging framework for their application, or they themselves can conform to this rule when writing a library.  In my case, since I am writing an IntelliJ IDEA plugin, I cannot include a backing logging framework in my dependency graph.  While I personally prefer logback,  I must use the logging framework built-in to the application.  When I use `jsemver` out of the box, I'm getting an [SLF4J multiple bindings error](http://www.slf4j.org/codes.html#multiple_bindings). While this is solved by adding an exclude to a build, it does place an unnecessary burden on the user of the `jsemver` library.

The easiest solution would be to make logback a `testRuntimeOnly` dependency and move the `logback.xml` file to `src\test\resources`.

issue_title: Cannot compile with picocli-shell-jline3 dependency using Maven
issue_body:
Since the change to [Fix gradle warnings](https://github.com/remkop/picocli/commit/758558b9817660b6c6e497aab28cb8ac7421127e), Maven compilation of any project with [picocli-shell-jline3](https://search.maven.org/search?q=a:picocli-shell-jline3) as a dependency is broken, since the artifact published to The Central Repository has a changed the scope of transitive dependencies to jline - see the following changes to scope in the published pom.xml:

```xml
    <dependency>
      <groupId>org.jline</groupId>
      <artifactId>jline</artifactId>
      <version>3.17.1</version>
      <scope>runtime</scope>
    </dependency>
```
whereas in former versions of picocli it was

```xml
    <dependency>
      <groupId>org.jline</groupId>
      <artifactId>jline</artifactId>
      <version>3.16.0</version>
      <scope>compile</scope>
    </dependency>
```

In order words, the change in how the Gradle dependency is defined has broken the Maven scope, and compilation fails.

issue_title: Consistent number of bombs
issue_body:
This is kind of subjective, but I think it would be nice to have control over the number of bombs that spawn. The way it is, you could have 1 bomb spawned or you could have 20, it's completely random. Which is fine, but you get much more control over the difficulty and nature of the game if you can specify the number of bombs to spawn.

One easy way to implement this, while making sure every cell has an equal chance of being a bomb, is:
- Let's say we have 100 cells, with indexes 0..99
- We want exactly 10 randomly chosen cells to be bombs and the rest empty
- Add those 100 indexes (integers) to a list
- Shuffle the list (`Collections.shuffle()`)
- The first 10 numbers in the list will be the indexes of our bomb cells

Now we can let the user choose easy (10 bombs), medium (15 bombs), hard (25 bombs) or whatever you want.

issue_title: [rllib] pytorch models not able to access batch['infos'] in custom_loss()
issue_body: I want to use the 'info' dictionary returned by the environment's step() function to define a custom loss. However, in torch_policy.py, custom_loss is being called on train_batch, which is a UsageTrackingDict. This makes it impossible to access the 'infos' of the batch, since it returns a tensor of objects, but UsageTrackingDict doesn't allow accessing tensors of objects. I can avoid this issue by using postprocessed_batch instead, but I'm wondering if there should be a better fix

issue_title: Input/Output Organization Issues
issue_body:
RIVET has improved a lot in recent months, and I believe that that it is now in good shape for practical use.  With that said, I believe RIVET might be more accessible to new users if the conventions for how data is input to/output from RIVET were reworked.  While these conventions may have been cohesive to start, they have evolved in a somewhat ad hoc fashion as we have introduced new features to RIVET over the past couple of years.  I think it would be good to take a careful look at them again. 

(This is related to some existing issues, namely issue #134, issue #130, issue #120, issue #121.) 

The issues I have in mind with how RIVET handles output are already summarized nicely the other issues linked above.  Below are some places where the input conventions could perhaps use further attention.

Input:
1)Right now, for input in the form of a point cloud or finite metric space, the kind of bifiltration you associate to the data is hard-coded in the input file.  In practice, one often wants to try several different bifiltrations (e.g., function-Rips with density function, degree-Rips, coeccentricity-Rips) with a single data data set.  Trying these different options ought to be as easy as easy as feeding a .csv file to RIVET and changing one command line option for different runs.  But right now, it's harder than this: For each of the three bifiltrations, you need to run a script (not currently included with RIVET) to construct three RIVET input files from the .csv.  Moreover,  the script has to compute the density functions or codensity functions on the vertices, as these are not computed natively by RIVET. 

This creates an unnecessary barrier to exploring data with RIVET.  The pyrivet API addresses this, which definitely helps, but I believe that the solution should be part of better input handling in RIVET itself.

2)The behavior of RIVET can be controlled in four different ways: 
* Command line options to rivet_console, 
* Specification of parameters in input files (e.g., axis labels, max distance parameter in a Rips bifiltration), 
* The file input dialogue in the GUI (this provides functionality equivalent to some but not all of the command line parameters for rivet_console),
* The preferences window in the GUI (for certain visualization parameters).

For the most part, on a case-by-case basis, the decisions about where to put a particular RIVET option seem reasonable, but I would feel better about the design if there were some clear overarching principles guiding these choices.  I believe that people getting to know the software for the first time may find it difficult to wrap their head around the different options and where they are located, especially since the way they are documented is (correspondingly) a bit scattered.

Here are some more concrete thoughts along these lines:

* It's not clear to me that it is best to distinguish command line options from the parameters given in an input file.  After all, some options (like max scale parameter, or choice of descending/ascending filtration for function-Rips bifiltration) would make equal sense in a file or from the command line (see issue #121).   Axis labels, which are currently part of the required data in an input file, may be unnecessary for some computations that avoid use of the visualization altogether.

Is there some principled way to unify the two types of input?  Perhaps everything could be a command line argument, and the user could have the option of putting command-line arguments in a file?  If we could defer enough of the arguments of a RIVET input file to the command line that RIVET could  comfortably handle an unadorned .csv file containing a point cloud or distance matrix, that would be great.  If this is not what we want to do, is there anyway to make our conventions more transparent / accessible?

3)Along similar lines, it would be nice if there were a way to yolk the options for the file input dialogue more tightly to the command-line options for RIVET.  In my experience, the file input dialogue makes using RIVET's visualization much easier; it is a valuable feature.  But from the development end, it is a bit cumbersome, because whenever a new command-line feature is implemented, there is the additional burden of having to decide whether to add it to the input dialogue.  For example, should I be able to control the number of processors used in parallel minimization of the presentation from the file input dialogue?  The problem will be further compounded when we introduce options to build several bifiltrations from a single data set, as suggested in 1).  Do we want to introduce special GUI elements for this in the file input dialogue?  This makes me wonder whether the GUI options in the input dialogue for choosing homology dimension and number of bins should be replaced with a text window to enter arbitrary command line options for rivet_console, together with some way to display the -h file which explains how to use these options.

4)Taking this idea one step further, perhaps following structure would be cleaner:
- The file input dialogue becomes a simple standalone wrapper to control rivet_console, and has exactly the same functionality as rivet_console, just in GUI.
- rivet_console gets a command line option to start the visualization, for suitable input.  (Perhaps this would be the default.)
-The visualization program rivet_GUI is stripped of the file input dialogue; it just opens module invariant files, and perhaps takes a signal from RIVET console telling it when then the augmented arrangement has been added to the module invariant file.

issue_title: Allow perfect (or close too) mirroring of dimensions
issue_body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
There is currently an issue where there is a prevalent rock layer between dimensions (when mirroring), I would like to see the ability once this is patched to perfectly mirror dimensions meaning they touch without a bedrock layer between.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
When a dimension is mirrored on top of another dimension there to be no bedrock layer or gap between the two, so they touch perfectly

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
Another solution could be to make it so the middle only forms if there are blocks directly above and below

**Additional context**
Add any other context or screenshots about the feature request here.
https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/295197386609917953/787274277170184202/2020-12-10_12.36.38.png

^ This is an example of the issue, I used a carve layer to remove the rock palette but it would be nice to allow them to touch.

issue_title: Tabs in docstrings are replaced with spaces
issue_body:
**Describe the bug** A clear and concise description of what the bug is.
When tabs are present in multiline function docstrings, black fails with
```
INTERNAL ERROR: Black produced code that is not equivalent to the source.
```

**To Reproduce** Steps to reproduce the behavior:
Run `black, version 20.8b1` on the following:
```
"""is	ok
"""

def fails():
    """a	b
    """

def is_ok():
    """a	b"""
```
(file embedded as .txt below)

1. Take this file

[tabcomment.txt](https://github.com/psf/black/files/5760976/tabcomment.txt)

2. Run _Black_ on it with these arguments (no arguments)
3. See error

**Expected behavior** A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen.
I would expect tabs to be replaced or preserved as black wishes, without errors.

**Environment (please complete the following information):**

- Version: `20.8b1`
- OS and Python version:  19.6.0 Darwin x86 / Python 3.9.0

**Does this bug also happen on master?**
No.  On master the multiline comment with tabs is converted to a single line comment with tabs.

```
"""is	ok
"""


def fails():
    """a	b"""


def is_ok():
    """a	b"""
```

**Additional context** Add any other context about the problem here.

issue_title: How to construct graphql query
issue_body: Hi, I am writing some tests and need to construct graphql query against my service, I am doing `format!` at the moment, but wondering if there is any composable way to construct the query, thanks!

issue_title: Optimize a dependency aliased to an absolute path
issue_body: I need to optimize `react` since it uses CommonJS modules, but I also need to force all packages to use the same copy of React, which I accomplish via the `alias` option in my Vite config. Unfortunately, these two needs are in conflict, as the import rewriter doesn't check if an absolute path is optimized.

issue_title: File structure under Maps to be reorganized
issue_body:
At the moment the file structure within `new-zealand-dataset > Maps` is difficult to navigate, due to the number of files.

This can easily be fixed by moving all of the ASMGCS views into a separate folder sorted by aerodrome. 

For example - 

    Maps/
        NZxx/
            ASMGCS_NZxx.xml
        NZxx/
            ASMGCS_NZxx.xml
    AIRPORTS.xml
    ASMGCS_TAXI_ALL.xml
    COAST.xml
    CTA.xml
    CTR.xml
    ENR_FREQ_LABELS.xml
    (and so on)

issue_title: [BUG] First waypoint is skipped?
issue_body:
<!-- ⚠⚠ Do not delete this issue template! ⚠⚠ -->

**Mod Version**

**Describe the bug**

I have done 2 flights in 1.9.3 and it seems that the first waypoint of the flightplan is skipped after take-off.

**To Reproduce**
<!-- Steps to reproduce the behavior. -->
<!-- We need to know how you encountered the bug to properly troubleshoot the issue. -->

I would expect the flightplan to follow the route to the first waypoint

**Actual behavior**

The plane skips the first waypoint and directly goes to the second one.

<!-- If applicable, add screenshots or videos to help explain your problem. -->

Was this working before/when did the issue start occurring?
First noticed this in 1.9.3

issue_title: [BUG] Pulling for Heading doesn't cause a reversion to open climb
issue_body:
<!-- ⚠⚠ Do not delete this issue template! ⚠⚠ -->

**Mod Version**
<!-- Either a release version or "master" for the latest master branch. -->
Latest

**Describe the bug**
<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->
When pulling for heading mode, the plane remains in managed climb rather than reverting to open climb.

**To Reproduce**
<!-- Steps to reproduce the behavior. -->
<!-- We need to know how you encountered the bug to properly troubleshoot the issue. -->
1.Fly in "NAV" and "CLB" (managed climb) modes.
2.Pull the heading knob to engage heading mode.
3.Note that "CLB" is still active and hasn't switched to open climb


**Expected behavior**
<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->
According to a real world Airbus pilot in the FBW discord, "Selecting HDG will give you a mode reversion from CLB to OPEN CLB. If you were in managed DEC you will get V/S."

**Actual behavior**

Plane remains in managed climb.

issue_title: Modify !anon set to take in multiple channels
issue_body:
Rather than running !anon set for each channel three times, we should provide users the ability to set all of them at once with one command.

The syntax for this could be either: `!anon set <anon-msgs> <deep-talks> <anon-logs>` or `!anon set all <anon-msgs> <deep-talks> <anon-logs>`

    --with-modules \

issue_title: BiocParallel: Workaround for assumptions on foreach error messages
issue_body:
# Background

**BiocParallel**'s DoParam backend assumes that the error messages produced by foreach match regular expression `task ([[:digit:]]+).*`, cf. https://github.com/Bioconductor/BiocParallel/issues/132.

# Suggestion

Add an R option `doFuture.workarounds` such that when using:

```r
options(doFuture.workarounds = c("BiocParallel.DoParam.errors"))`
```

with corresponding `R_DOFUTURE_WORKAROUNDS` environment variable (comma separated).

**doFuture** will prefix also its FutureError messages with `task <index>` such that **BiocParallel** won't choke on such errors.

issue_title: BiocParallel: Workaround for assumptions on foreach error messages
issue_body:
# Background

**BiocParallel**'s DoParam backend assumes that the error messages produced by foreach match regular expression `task ([[:digit:]]+).*`, cf. https://github.com/Bioconductor/BiocParallel/issues/132.

issue_title: [Feature] Backup and restore
issue_body:
Allow users to back up all their name lists to Google Drive/external SD card similar to Simple Flashcards Plus. Some thoughts:
1. Let's do it in Kotlin.
2. Let's mirror the UI in Simple Flashcards Plus as well (expose option in settings, add option to bottom sheet and homepage).
3. Need to make sure that the backup doesn't happen on main thread.
4. There's a lot to the lists schema now, especially if the user has premium. Keep that all in mind.
5. You can easily test this by creating some lists, backing it up, and then clearing the storage on your app to simulate a fresh install.
6. This is a huge feature. We will need to do development on a separate branch.
7. Gate it to just premium users. So when they tap on any of the entry points, we should point them to premium page if they don't have it.

issue_title: MIDI Instrument
issue_body:
The Instrument class in VSynth does not support many features required of the MIDI standard. This includes: Note velocities, Pitch Bends, Patch/Program changes. The polyphonic instrument class in VSynth is not the most efficient to use for the MIDI standard as well. The polyphonic instrument class uses mutexes to turn on and off notes. This works well when there is a large or infinite number of possible notes, but the MIDI standard only has 128. It would be more efficient to ditch the mutexes for the MIDI standard.

Related Issues:
#20

issue_title: MIDI Patches
issue_body: MIDI file format has a selection of 128 instruments an artist can choose from. Each of the 128 instruments can be divided into approximately 16 categories. You can find more in this link [MIDI Patches/Program change Events](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_MIDI#Program_change_events).

issue_title: MIDI Sequencer
issue_body:
The sequencer provided by my VSynth library only supports note On/Off events. The MIDI format has many events that should be taken into account (Program Change, Pitch Bend, etc.). A new MIDI Sequencer class should be created to make use of these. Similarly, MIDI Note On events take a velocity as a parameter. The velocity can change how loud the note is played, which cannot be supported by the base Sequencer class.

Related Issues:
#21

issue_title: WAV recorder
issue_body: A WAV recorder will allow us to output the synthesized music created by VSynth into a .WAV. This would be a big addition, especially for the MIDI player created by this library. We may want to consider using the Middleware addition discussed in #10

issue_title: Pulse and Noise waveforms
issue_body:
Two interesting waveforms to add would be the Pulse and Noise waveforms.

The pulse waveform is similar to the square waveform, but instead of being on and off 50% of the time, it can be specified. (e.g. a 80% on 20% off). 

The noise waveform is a random number generator. It works great for percussive sounding instruments.

issue_title: Tone Sound Generator
issue_body:
A simple tone sound generator would be a nice addition as well as an easy way to introduce people to the synth. The tone sound generator will output some waveform passed in through its constructor. Unlike the instrument sound generator, it does not need an envelope.

The tone interface should look something like this.

Tone(wave); // Create a tone object with the given waveform
Tone.play(frequency); // Play the wave at the specified frequency
Tone.stop(frequency); // Stop playing the wave at the specified frequency

Segmentation fault on iOS in AR
issue_body:
Hi all. Having a very inconsistent issue using AR foundation and our company iPad. Having seg faults on 
- [ARSession _sessionDidUpdateAnchors:]

Unfortunately it's so wildly inconsistent as to when it happens, it's hard to sort of pin down what may be causing this from our app. In terms of information of our app:

Using AR Foundation 4.0.9
Unity version 2020.1.14f

The use case for the app is just scanning images and creating objects where the images are. We do make the objects orbit the point where it has found the images but nothing too complex. The last crash happened after an image was scanned (we create an object at this point and give it the same position/rotation as the detected image). I've attached the crash log that came out of the iPad. 

I found one other person that had a similar issue but that was two years back:
https://forum.unity.com/threads/arkit-2-0-beta-support.534639/page-4

We were using ARAnchors, however when we started getting this error popping up I commented all of them out. It stopped for a while but it ended up popping up again. 

Not entirely certain what is causing this because it's so inconsistent in terms of when it happens. Any ideas/suggestions for this?

[crashreport.txt](https://github.com/Unity-Technologies/arfoundation-samples/files/5713714/crashreport.txt)

issue_title: Session/Speaker: Distinguish Private and Public Info Pages/Views and Separate Them
issue_body:
In previous iterations we focused on the views of the public information of sessions and speakers, e.g. shown on the schedule and public session page. However, the speaker can enter much more information than should be publicly available in their call for speakers response. 

Right now we do not show to the speaker which information is public or privately shown to the review team. We also do not have a page to show the session and speaker information which includes the private info. It is only possible to see the private info
if the speaker or organizer/reviewer edits sessions/speakers info.

Therefore we need to change and tweak a number of things in different areas. (Please open sub-issues where necessary)
1. In the wizard step 5 session and speaker forms please add a column "Show Public" to display a field publicly. If this is chosen show the field on the public session or speaker page. In a first step we could simply decide which info is public or private by default show the info "public" or "private" instead of a switch button.
2. Session View page and Session Edit page are confusing - we added the same functionality under different URLs, e.g. compare https://eventyay.com/e/598/cfs/session/5057/edit and https://eventyay.com/events/3689bc98/sessions/5057/edit. Whereas we only have one (public) page to view the session page here https://eventyay.com/e/3689bc98/session/5057 without showing the private form fields. What to do?
* We need to distinguish public and private pages and views. 
  * Public page view is on a page for attendees of an event. It only includes essential information and fields marked as "public" in the wizard.
  * Private page view is a page for speakers and organizers/reviewers. It includes all submitted information.
* Where to put private vs. public view page and which one can be edited?
  * Public pages are part of an event and can continue to stay on pages such as this one here https://eventyay.com/e/3689bc98/session/5057. These pages should not have an edit or withdraw button. They are just there to show information to attendees.
  * Private pages as in the above case the private submission page should be here as in this example https://eventyay.com/events/3689bc98/sessions/5057/ They should include an edit and withdraw button 
  * In the above example the editable version would be available here https://eventyay.com/events/3689bc98/sessions/5057/edit
* When a user submits a session to the call for speakers, session page and speaker page should be created according to the event. They should not follow the cfs slug. Speaker and organizers can both edit the session. Once marked as "Locked" only the organizer can edit it.

Compare:
* Private session page - Access by speaker and organizers
/events/[event-number]/sessions/[session-number]/
/events/[event-number]/sessions/[session-number]/edit
* Public - Public Access
eventyay.com/e/[event-number]/session/[session-number]
(no edit page)

See below: We need one more column "public" in the forms. Public links are shown on the public speaker info. Non-public are only shown to organizers.
![Screenshot from 2020-11-01 05-46-36](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1583873/97795369-adba1600-1c05-11eb-8387-ba18897fc15d.png)

The following fields need to be public always:
* [ ] Name
* [ ] Short bio
* [ ] Title
* [ ] Short Abstract

The info that a field is "public" should be shown on the call for speakers in brakets, e.g. _(public)_

issue_title: Non-reproducible outputs from adjoint solver (memory leak?)
issue_body:
Under certain conditions, when I create an an `OptimizationProblem` instance `opt = mpa.OptimizationProblem(...)` and then run `opt([x])` multiple times, the result can be very different for the first run (often `nan`), e.g. if I run

```python
x1 = np.ones(dv.Nx*dv.Ny) * (n_SiO2**2 + n_air**2)/2
print("Run 1")
(J0_a, dJ_a, dg_a) = opt([x1])
print("Run 2")
(J0_b, dJ_b, dg_b) = opt([x1])
print("Run 3")
(J0_c, dJ_c, dg_c) = opt([x1])
```

I find that `dJ_a` differs from `dJ_b`, `dJ_c` and is often very large, `inf`, or `nan`.  It's only the calculation of `dJ` that gets messed up; the actual simulations look fine (figures below).  One possibility is `meep.adjoint` is reading from the array memory that hasn't been initialized or is already freed (I've run into this with autograd elsewhere).

[Note14b-dJ.pdf](https://github.com/NanoComp/meep/files/4823092/Note14b-dJ.pdf)
[Note14b-sims.pdf](https://github.com/NanoComp/meep/files/4823094/Note14b-sims.pdf)

Full code below:

```python
import numpy as np
import meep as mp
import sys
sys.path.append("/Users/ryan.hamerly/Documents/Research/Code/meep/python")
import adjoint as mpa
import autograd.numpy as npa
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Global Constants
lam = 0.532;     f0 = 1/lam;      df = 0.2*f0;       res = 20

n_SiO2 = 1.45;   SiO2 = mp.Medium(index=n_SiO2)
n_air  = 1.00;   air  = mp.Medium(index=n_air)
n_Si   = 3.50;   Si   = mp.Medium(index=n_Si)

dpml = 1
(sx, sy) = (10, 7.7)
(Sx, Sy) = (sx+2*dpml, sy+2*dpml)

#%%

dr_res = 2*res
dr = mp.Volume(center=mp.Vector3(0, 2.4), size=mp.Vector3(sx, 0.9))
dv = mpa.BilinearInterpolationBasis(volume=dr, resolution=dr_res)

geom = [mp.Block(size=dr.size, center=dr.center, epsilon_func=dv.func())]
src_gauss = mp.Source(mp.GaussianSource(f0, fwidth=df),
                      center=mp.Vector3(0, sy/2-0.1), size=mp.Vector3(sx, 0), component=mp.Ez)

sim = mp.Simulation(cell_size=mp.Vector3(Sx, Sy),
                    resolution=res,
                    boundary_layers=[mp.PML(dpml)],
                    geometry=geom,
                    sources=[src_gauss],
                    default_material=SiO2,
                    eps_averaging=False)

TE0 = mpa.EigenmodeCoefficient(sim, mp.Volume(mp.Vector3(0, -sy/2+1), size=mp.Vector3(lam*0.7, 0)), mode=1,
                               eig_parity=mp.ODD_Z, k0=mp.Vector3(0, -1))
ob_list = [TE0]
def J(alpha):
    return npa.abs(alpha)**2

opt = mpa.OptimizationProblem(sim, J, ob_list, [dv], fcen=f0, df=0, nf=1, decay_fields=[mp.Ez])

#%%  Now run the simulation 3 times with the same data.

print("************************* First run of opt([x1]) *************************")
x1 = np.ones(dv.Nx*dv.Ny) * (n_SiO2**2 + n_air**2)/2
(J0_a, dJ_a, dg_a) = opt([x1])

print("************************* Second run of opt([x1]) *************************")
x1 = np.ones(dv.Nx*dv.Ny) * (n_SiO2**2 + n_air**2)/2
(J0_b, dJ_b, dg_b) = opt([x1])

print("************************* Third run of opt([x1]) *************************")
x1 = np.ones(dv.Nx*dv.Ny) * (n_SiO2**2 + n_air**2)/2
(J0_c, dJ_c, dg_c) = opt([x1])

#%%  Show the derivatives dJ/d_epsilon for the three (identical) trials

(f, axList) = plt.subplots(3, 1, sharex=True, sharey=True)
for (ax, dJ, ttl) in zip(axList, [dJ_a, dJ_b, dJ_c], ["Run 1", "Run 2", "Run 3"]):
    cax = ax.imshow(np.squeeze(dJ).T, origin='lower', aspect='auto', cmap='seismic');
    ax.set_xticks([]); ax.set_yticks([]); ax.set_title(ttl)
    f.colorbar(cax, ax=ax)
plt.savefig("Note14b-dJ.pdf")
#plt.show()

#%%  Simulation setup, forward and adjoint runs

print("************************* Forward run *************************")
(f, (ax1, ax2)) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(8, 4), sharex=True, sharey=True)
opt.prepare_forward_run()
opt.sim.run(until=20)
opt.sim.plot2D(ax=ax1, fields=mp.Ez, eps_parameters=dict(cmap='binary_r'))
print("************************* Adjoint run *************************")
opt.adjoint_run()
opt.sim.reset_meep()
opt.sim.run(until=20)
opt.sim.plot2D(ax=ax2, fields=mp.Ez, eps_parameters=dict(cmap='binary_r'))
ax1.set_title("Forward Run, $t=20$"); ax2.set_title("Adjoint Run, $t=20$"); ax2.set_ylabel("")
f.tight_layout(); f.savefig("Note14b-sims.pdf")
#plt.show()
```

issue_title: runtime warning for DFT routines due to Fourier uncertainty principle
issue_body:
As demonstrated in [Tutorial/Custom Source/Stochastic Dipole Emission in Light Emitting Diodes](https://meep.readthedocs.io/en/latest/Python_Tutorials/Custom_Source/#stochastic-dipole-emission-in-light-emitting-diodes), the runtime of any simulation involving DFT monitors must be at least ~1/frequency resolution due to the Fourier Uncertainty Principle. (The LED tutorial example involved a flux spectra with fine features which required a longer runtime of 2/frequency resolution to produce results with sufficient accuracy.) The key point is that this minimum runtime is due to a property of the signal processing and is independent of whether the fields in the simulation have decayed away to e.g. 1e-10 or not (i.e., when using the `stop_when_fields_decayed` [run function](https://meep.readthedocs.io/en/latest/Python_User_Interface/#run-functions)). Users performing a [convergence check](https://meep.readthedocs.io/en/latest/FAQ/#checking-convergence) in which they are just doubling the runtime can overlook this point and inadvertently choose a runtime which is too short.

It might therefore be helpful, particularly for novice users, if Meep issued a runtime warning for the DFT routines `get_fluxes`, `get_eigenmode_coefficients`, `get_farfields`, etc. whenever the simulation time at the moment these routines are invoked is less than 1/frequency resolution so that the user is aware that the frequency spectra may be inaccurate. (Such a runtime warning could only be shown if e.g. the `verbosity` flag is larger 1.)

Additionally, another useful runtime warning would be if the inverse of the temporal resolution Δt (=CΔx where C is the [Courant factor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Courant%E2%80%93Friedrichs%E2%80%93Lewy_condition) and Δx is the Yee grid resolution) is smaller than the largest frequency in the DFT frequency grid.

issue_title: Using magickload with vips cli doesn't auto rotate images
issue_body:
Using vips CLI to load an image via `magickload` and then save it in a different format doesn't auto-rotate the output. 

Convert command: `vips magickload image.jpg image.png`

running `vipsheader -a image.jpg` outputs the orientation: `orientation: 8`
running the same on the output: `vipsheader -a image.png` gives no orientation tag. 
Looks like all of the metadata is gone. 

 - OS:  MacOS 11.1
 - Vips: 8.11

issue_title: Please add an environment variable that specifies a site_scons directory
issue_body:
This issue was originally created at: 2014-06-25 22:53:04.
This issue was reported by: `mattaw`.
mattaw said at 2014-06-25 22:53:04
>- I am working with an SoC design using SCons to manage the build cleanly.
>- I have added SCons to the repo to ensure that every user is using my preferred
>version of SCons.
>- I supply the necessary builders/scanners/etc. for HDL simulation and synth in
>the repo.
>- I cannot expect the normal user (without admin permissions) to be able to
>install to the systemwide site_scons.
>- I find it consistently awkward to constantly add --site-dir=<blah> or modify
>the environment to append it whenever scons is called.
>- ~/.scons is unsuitable as it would not be managed by the repo and new features
>and bugfixes for the HDL builders are being added fairly quickly.
> 
>The cleanest solution used by most tools on most platforms would be an
>environment variable.
> 
>Thanks!
> 
>Matthew

dirkbaechle said at 2014-06-26 00:11:39
>Hi,
> 
>do you already know that you can set the search path to tools in an Environment 
>with the "toolpath" variable?
>This should be what you're looking for, or are there some other problems that I 
>don't see?
> 
>If possible, it would be good to discuss these kinds of ideas and suspected bugs 
>on the User mailing list first. Thanks for reporting it anyway.
> 
>Best regards,
> 
>Dirk

bdbaddog said at 2014-06-26 11:28:42
>Seems a reasonable request.
>Are you aware that SCons already does look for site_scons in the directory where
>the SConstruct lives?
> 
>From Manpage:
>Before reading the SConstruct file, scons looks for a directory named site_scons
>in various system directories (see below) and the directory containing the
>SConstruct file; for each of those dirs which exists, site_scons is prepended to
>sys.path, the file site_scons/site_init.py, is evaluated if it exists, and the
>directory site_scons/site_tools is prepended to the default toolpath if it
>exists. See the --no-site-dir and --site-dir options for more details.

mattaw said at 2014-06-26 12:45:24
>Firstly please forgive me for overlooking the toolpath. I delved through the 
>source and looked at everything and never even thought about just appending the 
>path to it inside the environment.
> 
>I have quickly implemented it and it kind of works for me however it requires 
>another 12 odd lines of code in each SConscript and the lines are all different 
>due to different levels of directory hierarchy.
> 
>I would suggest for the "reduce the LOC in the SConscript" and to avoid lots of 
>repetitions of similar code the envrionment variable would work better.
> 
>Thanks for your assitance so far, let me know what you think.
> 
>Matthew

dirkbaechle said at 2014-06-26 13:05:59
>This sounds as if you're initializing new Environments in each and every one of 
>your SConscripts...which isn't necessary.
>Start at the top-level SConstruct, and set up a "base" Environment with the 
>required tools. Then pass this Environment down to your SConscripts.
> 
>Can we switch this conversation to the User mailing list, because writing back 
>and forth is a little awkward within the Tigris tracker? Just refer to this issue 
>and continue to ask your questions there, please.

bdbaddog said at 2014-06-26 14:54:21
>Actually as Dirk suggested. It's always best to bring your issues to the users
>mailing list first to see if they can be resolved, you'll get far more eyes on
>them there.
> 
>Also, I'm changing the type to enhancement request.

bdbaddog said at 2017-03-21 12:10:32
>Did you end up resolving this via discussion in users mailing list?
>If so, please close the bug?
>If not, let us know..

mattaw said at 2017-03-21 17:44:35
>Actually due to the need to replace some core bits of scons to handle the concept 
>of a sim library as the basic unit instead of a single file I migrated to waf. 
>Unfortunately there are just too many places where scons modules expect an object 
>to have internal structures and data in the same place instead of calling 
>functions exposed by the object in the normal OO way.
> 
>Best, please close if needed.

issue_title: Remove Android Kotlin Extensions Gradle plugin
issue_body:
[Support for it has ended](https://android-developers.googleblog.com/2020/11/the-future-of-kotlin-android-extensions.html) and both Google and JetBrains encourage to use [View Binding](https://developer.android.com/topic/libraries/view-binding).

We have around 10 files using synthetics that need to be migrated. Ideally we switch it to view binding instead of `findViewById` calls. 

The dependency is added in this line, removing it will show all usages of synthetics in the form of compiler errors:

https://github.com/jellyfin/jellyfin-androidtv/blob/19cf80579b04b2d4c4f4af462bfc8e169623c808/app/build.gradle.kts#L4

issue_title: Live TV plays using audio description audio track
issue_body:
This is likely very related to #3765, but I thought it was worth reporting as it could also be considered a bug that needs to be fixed.

**Describe the bug**
When playing UK satellite TV channels in live TV, Jellyfin transcodes and plays the 'audio description' (nar) audio track, not the expected English audio track.

As a result the live TV channels are unwatchable (unless you're someone who wants audio description).

The live TV source is TVHeadend, but TVHeadend is passing through the raw TS stream for the channels, so I'd expect the same result with other source software.

**System (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: Ubuntu 20.04
 - Virtualization: Docker
 - Clients: Browser
 - Browser: Edge 84
 - Jellyfin Version: 10.6.0
 - Playback: Transcode
 - Installed Plugins: None
 - Reverse Proxy: None
 - Base URL: None
 - Networking: Bridge
 - Storage: N/A

**To Reproduce**
1. Go to the live TV library
2. Play a live TV channel that is broadcasting with an audio description track

**Expected behavior**
The live TV channel should play with the default English audio track, not the audio description track. Alternatively Jellyfin should provide a choice of audio track.

**Additional context**
VLC also defaults to the audio description track, and FFmpeg puts it as the first audio stream, so this is more of an FFmpeg issue than a Jellyfin one, but it's one Jellyfin will need to work around.

I'm willing to help tackle this one myself, but I'm not currently sure where to start, at least not in a way that works for all languages.

issue_title: DLNA Playback Not Working?
issue_body:
**Describe the bug**
<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->
This problem only started when i upgraded JF. I just recently upgraded from JF 10.5.2.1 to 10.5.3.1. Thats when i started getting this error. Everytime i play a movie or tv show it will play fine the first time ever playing it. But lets say i backout of that movie/tv show. Load somethin else up. Then go back to that same Season and Episode i just watch before i backed out to the main menu. It will not load and give me an error saying, "It will try to load then give me an error saying. "This file cannot be recognized. Do you want to play the next file?" theres an option to select Yes or No. I used the example log from my jellyfin log using Band of Brothers S01E03. Please fix. Let me know if theres anything else you need.

**System (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: [Ubuntu 18.04]
 - Virtualization: [None]
 - Clients: [Browser, Android, LG DLNA, Xbox One,]
 - Browser: Firefox 72, Chrome 80, Safari 13, WebOS LG DLNA]
 - Jellyfin Version: [10.5.3.1]
 - Playback: [Direct Play, Direct Stream, Transcode] 
 - Installed Plugins: [Audio DB, Auto Organize, Email Notifications, LDAP-Auth(currently working on), Music Brains, Open Subtitles, TMDB Boxsets, GoNotify]
 - Reverse Proxy: [apache]
 - Base URL: [stream.movies4you (configured through apache not through jellyfin admin)]
 - Networking: [HostName Router Configured]
 - Storage: [local, NFS, cloud]

**To Reproduce**
<!-- Steps to reproduce the behavior: -->
1. Go to Any acceptable DLNA Device accessable on the network.
2. Connect to DLNA JF server.
3. Go to Movies/TV Shows
4. Click on one that no one has viewed yet.
5. Click Play. It will play just fine.
6. Go back to main menu of JF DLNA server.
7. Click back on Movies/TV Shows.
8. Load back up the Movie/TV Show i was watching.
9. It will try to load then give me an error saying. "This file cannot be recognized. Do you want to play the next file?" theres an option to select Yes or No.
10. I just recently upgraded from JF 10.5.2.1 to 10.5.3.1. Thats when i started getting this error.

**Expected behavior**
<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->
I should be able to click on lets say a Movies in my movie sections ie. Forest Gump. It will play and then i pause it. Then go back lets say i wanna watch a different tv show ie. Band of Brothers S1E2. So i play it. No matter if i go back 30 second later or 7hrs later. I should be able to go back to movies and continue watching Forest gump from where i paused it. 
**Logs**
<!-- Please paste any log errors. -->

issue_title: Problem with LovaszLossBinary
issue_body:
There is a problem with LovaszLossBinary(maybe there are similar problems with LovaszLossMultiClass and LovaszLossMultiLabel)

If I train a model using lovasz loss, I don't have any problems. If I use a combination of several losses(for example bce, dice, iou) and use MetricAggregationCallback, I will get such error:
================================================
RuntimeError: Expected object of scalar type Double but got scalar type Float for sequence element 3 in sequence argument at position #1 'tensors'
================================================
I use this code:
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
criterion = {
    "dice": DiceLoss(),
    "iou": IoULoss(),
    "bce": nn.BCEWithLogitsLoss(),
    "lovasz": LovaszLossBinary()
}
callbacks = [
    # Each criterion is calculated separately.
    CriterionCallback(
        input_key="mask",
        prefix="loss_lovasz",
        criterion_key="lovasz"
    ),
    CriterionCallback(
        input_key="mask",
        prefix="loss_iou",
        criterion_key="iou"
    ),
    CriterionCallback(
        input_key="mask",
        prefix="loss_bce",
        criterion_key="bce"
    ),
    CriterionCallback(
        input_key="mask",
        prefix="loss_dice",
        criterion_key="dice"
    ),

    MetricAggregationCallback(
        prefix="loss",
        mode="weighted_sum",
        metrics={"loss_dice": 1.0, "loss_iou": 1.0, "loss_bce": 0.8, "loss_lovasz": 1.0},
    ),
]
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
I think it caused by the fact that this loss returns 'torch.cuda.FloatTensor' while other return 'torch.cuda.DoubleTensor'
I solve this problem by using a simple helped class:
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
from catalyst.contrib.nn.criterion import LovaszLossBinary

class LovaszLoss(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, per_image=False):
        super(LovaszLoss, self).__init__()
        self.lovasz = LovaszLossBinary(per_image)
    
    def forward(self, logits, target):
        return self.lovasz(logits, target).double()
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
After this, all work well

issue_title: Unexpected error during NotifRespond() with invalid argument
issue_body:
Hi!

I am trying to incorporate sysbox in to buildroot on a custom kernel and for the most part it is going okay.

The kernel is 5.4.81 and I have ported shiftfs from Ubuntu in to the kernel as well as enabled all SECCOMP config options.  Sysbox is build from the Makefile and the completed binaries from the docker file included in the final output as well as systemd unit files.

The good news is everything runs.  sysbox-mgr and sysbox-fs are started at boot and specifying sysbox-runc as the runtime correctly initializes the container.

The problem is, however, when it comes to doing any type of file operations.  In the logs of sysbox-fs.log I see:

Unexpected error during NotifRespond() execution (invalid argument) on fd 13 pid 3289

With the result that any operation requiring writing files (apk add, for example) is halted inside the container.

I've spent two days prodding this and that with no success.  Is there any recommendation on what I can do to assist in debugging or any ideas of where to look further?

Any help would be greatly appreciated :)

issue_title: Clarify what save/load grid vs save/load morph set really means

save/load grid currently lets you save a  whole grid, but that is wrong.

Really a grid is just a row -- it is the start or end point of a morph.

saving or loading the grid,  should be done via saving and loading a morph set. because thats what a morph set is, a set of rows interpolating from a start row to an end row.

So, rename save/load grid to save/load row (end either disable when a morph set is defined, or enable picking a specific row to save)

issue_title: Redeclaring a layout fragment in a decoration template that is part of a hierarchy of nested templates yields the wrong results
issue_body:
Having a template in a hierarchy of nested templates, that redeclares a layout fragment that was already declared in the decorated base template at the root of the hierarchy, and with the content template once again declaring the same layout fragment, the fragment declared by the decorated template will be used instead of that from the content template. Example ``` # Test a deep layout hierarchy (3 levels) with redeclaration of layout fragments. %TEMPLATE_MODE HTML %INPUT Page title

Page content

Page footer

%INPUT[Parent]

My website

Parent content

Parent footer

%INPUT[Grandparent]

Grandparent section

Grandparent footer

%OUTPUT Page title

My website

Page content

Page footer

``` The above will fail with the following output ``` Obtained: [ion>

Parent footer

Page footer

``` A remedy for this is to change the FragmentProcessor to use the last fragment instead of the first, e.g. ``` def fragment = fragments.size() == 1 ? fragments.first() : fragements.last() ``` Doing so will make the tests for infinite loops fail, so this might be more involved.

issue_title: Transaction daytrade calculation doesn't allow for deleting transactions
issue_body:
## Problem
The way calculation for transaction daytrade currently works doesn't allow for gracefully deleting transactions and keeping a consistent state of which transactions are daytrade or not anymore.

##How it works currently
Currently they are calculated by some convoluted way that gets "available daytrade space" from same day other type transactions than the new one being registered and changes them accordingly without concern for transactions that have already filled up their "daytrade space". This is more performant than recalculating everything from the start for the transactions of the same date as the new one, but it overcomplicates logic for removing transactions where that might cause other transactions to "unbecome" daytrade transactions. Also, that performance is not crucial as the number of same day transactions should not go over a point where it can make a perceivable performance impact by recalculating everything every time.

issue_title: Cleric does not have Turn option in battle
issue_body:
Filling this after fixing:  

Cleric did not have the Turn option in the combat menu.  After debugging, found that COMBAT_DATA::CanTurnUndead() was failing because the CAN_TURN hook was returning "".  Because RunCombatantScripts() was being called instead, and I think all those hookse are under the "Competing" SA, I moved [CanTurn] and [TurnAttempt] up to "Competing" and was able to get it to work.

- Accepts mixed case response for skip and fight.

issue_title: Fight/Skip prompt response
issue_body:
## Expected Behavior
If the prompt for the player is left blank or cancelled, a new prompt should re-request the player action if it is not valid

## Current Behavior
* if prompt for player action is left black, canceled, or not given 'SKIP' or 'skip' it will fight the match.
* if player action is to skip, it skips.

## Possible Solution
* Create function getPlayerAction() function that will loop until a valid response can be returned

issue_title: CSV Importer: cURL error 6: Could not resolve host with docker-compose
issue_body:
I am running the current docker image (latest tag)

**Description**
First off: Thanks for the amazing software! I stumbled yesterday about firefly and the setup was straight forwar over docker-compose. I tried today to enable the CSV Importer and I am stuck already for hours without knowing what I am doing wrong.
As I said I used docker-compose to set-up firefly and tried to use the docker image of the CSV Importer to import data. The Webserver is also opening but I get the error message: `cURL error 6: Could not resolve host: %20http (see https://curl.haxx.se/libcurl/c/libcurl-errors.html) for %20http://fireflyiii:8080/api/v1/about`
I changed the URI already in every way that seems logic to me so I used the internal docker URL that I received from this command `docker inspect -f '{{range .NetworkSettings.Networks}}{{.IPAddress}}{{end}}' CONTAINER`
I tried to not start the container stand-alone but with docker-compose so that the services are in the same virtual network. I used the http://fireflyiii:8080 URI but so far nothing worked. I also tried running it inline but I get the same error message in the CL.

**My guess**
I think this has to do something with the virtual network that got created trough docker-compose. But I am also not sure if the API is working. It seems I can't browse the endpoints with the browser and sadly I have not the possibility to install postman on my machine.

Here is my latest docker-compose file (with my trial to insert the csvimporter into the same virtual network):

version: '3.3'

services:
  fireflyiii:
    image: jc5x/firefly-iii:latest
    volumes:
      - firefly_iii_upload:/var/www/html/storage/upload
    env_file: .env
    ports:
      - 8030:8080
    depends_on:
      - fireflyiiidb
  fireflyiiidb:
    image: yobasystems/alpine-mariadb:latest
    environment:
      - MYSQL_RANDOM_ROOT_PASSWORD=yes
      - MYSQL_USER=firefly
      - MYSQL_PASSWORD=secret_firefly_password
      - MYSQL_DATABASE=firefly
    volumes:
      - firefly_iii_db:/var/lib/mysql
  csvimporter:
    image: fireflyiii/csv-importer:latest
    environment: 
      - FIREFLY_III_ACCESS_TOKEN=eyJ...
      - FIREFLY_III_URL=http://172.18.0.4:8080
    ports:
      - 8031:8080

volumes:
   firefly_iii_upload:
   firefly_iii_db:

The .env file is the same as from the repo, I just changed the language settings.

issue_title: select,date-picker,month-picker,range-picker,week-picker 在自定义指令中绑定change 事件不生效
issue_body:
- [ ] I have searched the [issues](https://github.com/vueComponent/ant-design-vue/issues)         of this repository and believe that this is not a duplicate.
        
        
### Version
2.0.0 及 1.5.1等以前版本，我只试到了1.4

### Environment
os: win10,   npm: 6.12.1  @vue/cli: 4.2.3, brower: chrome 78.0.3904.97（Official Build） （64 ビット）

### Reproduction link
[![Edit on CodeSandbox](https://codesandbox.io/static/img/play-codesandbox.svg)](https://codesandbox.io/s/vue-antd-template-ecwpj?file=/src/App.vue)

### Steps to reproduce
参考 [重现链接](https://codesandbox.io/s/vue-antd-template-ecwpj?file=/src/App.vue)

### What is expected?
自定义指令绑定事件，正常生效

### What is actually happening?
自定义指令绑定事件，没有效果

---
场景：自定义指令实现所有 validation check统一管理，通过配置文件进行集成，同时绑定触发事件（change、blur...）和 触发参数

eg:  v-validate.change="'xxx'"

目前测试结果：
input 、checkbox，checkbox group 绑定正常
select、所有日期相关（date-picker）等绑定失败

临时解决方案：

node_modules\ant-design-vue\es\select\index.js

L119-L122 =>
```
// FIXME: fire change for select component
fireChange: function fireChange(value) {
    this.$emit('change', value);
},
```
L253-L257 =>
```
// FIXME: fire change for select component
// on: getListeners(this),
on:_extends({}, getListeners(this), {
    change: this.fireChange
}),
```
node_modules\ant-design-vue\es\date-picker\wrapPicker.js

L104-L107 =>
```
// FIXME: fire change for select component
fireChange: function fireChange(e) {
    this.$emit('change', arguments[0], arguments[1]);
},
```
L196-L197 =>
```
// FIXME: fire change for select component
change: this.fireChange,
```
希望作者大大能够官方提供事件穿透  ：）

issue_title: Safari on macOS experience serious performance problem on scrolling.
issue_body: **Describe The Bug** Scrolling on Safari on macOS is now extremely slow, at about 10fps(or lower). The inspector says most of the time is spent on style recalculation and that takes hundreds of milliseconds per frame. **Steps To Reproduce** 1. Launch Safari 2. Go to Jellyfin website 3. Scroll at homepage 4. Experiencing very low frame-rate **Expected Behavior** Due to the number of images we have on the homepage, I don't expect we could get solid 60fps in most cases, but I do think we can have a performance better than currently we have. **Logs** No logs **Screenshots** **System (please complete the following information):** - Platform: macOS 10.15.6 - Browser: Safari 14 - Jellyfin Version: 10.6.4 **Additional Context** An interesting fact is that this does not happen on iOS Safari, and iOS Safari is having butter-smooth scrolling, only a few frames recalculates the styles. Chrome on macOS does perform better, but it does not support alac streaming.

issue_title: New want: Execute another web page within a secure headless context
issue_body:
---
title: Execute another web page within a secure headless context
date: 2020-04-13T01:59:22.839Z
submitter: PRIVATE
number: 5e93c77a76ae4c1a4ed515ed
tags: []
---

I would like to make a tool to retrieve metadata from websites. Unfortunately, when a page is rendered with JavaScript, like https://twitter.com/webwewantfyi/status/1131998584147070976, the metadata is not available until the JavaScript has been executed. 

CORS (https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/CORS) allows for sharing resources  across origins. However, even with that ability, all that can be retrieved from another site is the raw HTML. While DOMParser (https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMParser) provides a way to parse the HTML into a DOM, it doesn't execute the HTML (or the attached JavaScript). Even if the HTML is completely readable by the other origin, it cannot execute it safely.

Downloaded applications, like Electron apps, could use Puppeteer https://pptr.dev/ without asking any additional permissions, to execute an HTML page and it's dependencies. However, a Progressive Web App is unable to do the same, despite having the browser already at it's disposal.

It would be incredible if the browser provide a "Headless API" that would allow for fetching and executing a resource in a worker thread, and giving the main thread access to the Document (assuming the response is non-opaque), but not the Window.

Since CORS already provides a mechanism to do this without execution, providing a mechanism to do so with execution does not create any additional security concerns. Dependencies would be opaque to the main thread unless the response had the proper CORS headers to be shared.

issue_title: [BUG] Dual engine failure during flight
issue_body:
<!-- ⚠⚠ Do not delete this issue template! ⚠⚠ -->
<!-- Issues that do not use the issue template are likely to be ignored and closed. -->


**Mod Version**
<!-- Either a release version or "master" for the latest master branch. -->
latest master, but also on previous versions.
Since the latest 1.9.3.0 release.

**Describe the bug**
<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->
See the video below. N2 and engine temperatures suddenly drop and both engines fail.
Tried with and without anti icing. and with and without icing settings in the settings.


**To Reproduce**
<!-- Steps to reproduce the behavior. -->
<!-- We need to know how you encountered the bug to properly troubleshoot the issue. -->
I got it first once like 3 days ago on a different flight, restarted the flight and it worked without issues.
But today I restarted this flight like 5 times and it would happen around the 8 minute mark after takeoff.
1. start a flight from EDDF to EHAM. Low altitude airways. Gate A18 Medium direct to direct ILS 27. Fuel at 9% and sky conditions high level clouds.
2. start from cold and dark get jetway baggage catering and taxi to runway 25C.
3. take off turn on autopilot follow altitudes and set throttle CLB.


**Expected behavior**
<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->
The engines shouldn't fail.

**Actual behavior**
<!-- A clear and concise description of what actually happened. -->
They fail.

Livery Ryan Air. AI traffic and ground aircraft off
will test next without the livery.

Was this working before/when did the issue start occurring?
it was working before.

Is this a problem in the vanilla unmodded game?
not sure. I will do more testing.
