[Feature Request] Note flag --add-notes in CLI to allow additional notes for each ledger entry
issue_body:
Would just like to tell you how much work you've saved me on importing bank statements (with 3 banks in various countries.). Love the gem.

One thing that would be helpful for me is that quite often the imported bank statements have nonsensical strings attached to them in the description fields or will be for someplace I don't go very often. It would be great if we could pass a flag that allows us to enter a note (or simply hit return to bypass that) and that got introduced into that entry. 
eg.
```
Misc DR-Debit Card AJI-ICHI SINGAPORE 28 FEB 4934 9430378
```

Could not remember for the life of me what this charge was until I googled and found out it was a random dinner near the Observatory when I went to do some star gazing (and was underwhelming). Being able to add in a note to the effect of `S Dinner @ Observatory outing` for entries when I puzzle them out would be amazing and super helpful when going back and looking at things.

(I checked this time and it doesn't "appear" that that feature is available, but it woudl be very awesome to have added in if possible. Especially for reconciliation purposes.)

thanks!

Станция определяется только если стереть файл manifest.js
issue_body:
Очень странный баг. Колонка яндекс мини. Сначала долго не мог настроить, потому что колонка работала день в HA, а потом терялась (видимо что-то с токеном). Чинилось удалением всех токенов и получением новых.
Потом оказалось, что вместо этого можно просто удалить файл manifest.js и все работает долго и без сбоев. Причем при каждом обновлении этот файл появляется снова, колонка теряется, я его удаляю и живу дальше с новой версией.
Я далек от программирования, но сама логика этого действия мне кажется странной.

issue_title: Включить плейлист пользователя
issue_body:
В автоматизацию ввёл:

```
  - data:
      entity_id: media_player.yandex_station_040078
      media_content_id: 1008    # ID альбома в Яндекс.Музыка
      media_content_type: playlist  # album, track or playlist

issue_title: Clarify documentation around "required" inverse relationships
issue_body:
Hi, and thanks for making CoreStore!

The documentation says:

> All relationships are required to have an "inverse" relationship.

However, I was able to create a schema where some of the relationships do not have inverses, and this did not result in any compiler or runtime errors. What's the deal?

issue_title: Human Race Bug
issue_body: When adding the Human Race to a character, its bonus skill point is not accounted for in the calculated total points available. This is easy to work around by adding it manually (by adding the missing total to the "Bonus Point Formula" box), but this seems like a bug since the Human Race _does_ account for other things, e.g. Feats.

issue_title: Concatenate nil value error casting spell from a macro
issue_body:
## Issue description:
Targeting a training dummy, and call a macro that calls the (Affliction) Warlock spell "Mortal Coil" (while having a Felhunter pet out) generates an "attempt to concatenate local 'charges' (a nil value)" error.

_Note that I am not in a party or raid at the time of the error._

Here is the macro ...

/cast Mortal Coil


I've confirmed that the macro does succeed, and the target dummy gets the debuff generated by the casting of the Mortal Coil spell.

## How to reproduce:
1. Create a macro with one line in it, "/cast Mortal Coil".
2. Put the macro on an action bar (I used bottom-right bar).
3. Target a 'Training Dummy' NPC (I used the one in The Royal Armory in Zandalar/Dazar'alor).
4. Start combat by pressing the button that has the macro placed on it.
5. Error happens immediately (its an instant cast spell).

## Technical info:
 - **Addon Version:** *3.3.2*
 - **Client:** *Retail*
 - **Client Patch Version:** *9.0.2.36949*
 
## Additional context:
List of active addons when the error condition happens ...

> Details (DetailsRetail.9.0.2.8097.144)
> Enhanced Raid Frames (3.3.2)
> GTFO (4.57.1)
> MoveAnything (18.0.4)
> PetTracker (9.0.6)
> Scrap (9.0.1)
> TellMeWhen (9.0.3)
> TomTom (v90002-1.2.0)

All addons were installed via the "[Ajour](https://www.getajour.com/)" (version 0.5.4) Windows app (as discussed [here](https://www.wowhead.com/news=318208/ajour-open-source-simple-world-of-warcraft-addon-manager)).

issue_title: [Date Picker] - Special characters appended to value in IE 11
issue_body:
### Description
While using date picker in IE 11, the selected date has special characters. You cant see in the console log but if you print the length, it has more than 10 characters. While sending the value in API request body, you could see the special characters get appended to the date string.

### Example
```javascript
2018?-?05-?11
```

### Temp solution
I came up with custom method on date selection

```javascript
  formatDate = (date) => {
    const dateExp = date.split('/');
    return `${dateExp[0].replace(/[^0-9]/g,"")}-${dateExp[1].replace(/[^0-9]/g,"")}-${dateExp[2].replace(/[^0-9]/g,"")}`
  }
```

### Version
- React - 16.3.1
- React-MD - 1.2.13
- Browser IE 11.0

issue_title: Command line tool: Help message should include version number
issue_body:
**Describe the bug**
When calling `tflite2onnx -h` it'd be useful to see the version number.

**Expected behavior**
```
tflite2onnx, Version 0.3.1 by jackwish, https://jackwish.net/tflite2onnx/
Convert TensorFlow Lite models to ONNX models

usage: tflite2onnx [-h] tflite_path onnx_path

positional arguments:
  tflite_path  Path to the input TFLite mode
  onnx_path    Path to save the converted ONNX mode

optional arguments:
  -h, --help   show this help message and exit
```

**Actual behavior**
```
usage: tflite2onnx [-h] tflite_path onnx_path

Convert TensorFlow Lite models to ONNX models

positional arguments:
  tflite_path  Path to the input TFLite mode
  onnx_path    Path to save the converted ONNX mode

optional arguments:
  -h, --help   show this help message and exit
```

**To Reproduce**
1. Invoke `tflite2onnx -h`

**Version**
v0.3.1

issue_title: Problem with ESP32_DEVKIT V4  WROOM & StepperDemo

Hello,
I want to run a single stepper (200 steps per turn; 1A current spec) using an DRV8824 powered at 12V for the motor (DRV8824 trimpot adjusted). 
I am using a win10 laptop and an Arduino environment.
When using an Arduino mega2560 hooked to a RAMPS card with A DRV8824, I get correct motion of the motor using a StepperDriver library (with acceleration/deceleration capability)

I want now to use a and an ESP32_DEVKIT V4  WROOM , and my goal is to use 6 steppers at 200 steps/turn, to rotate concurently each with an eventual different speed in the range 20RPM-800RPM

issue_title: Problem with ESP32_DEVKIT V4  WROOM & StepperDemo
issue_body:
Hello,
I want to run a single stepper (200 steps per turn; 1A current spec) using an DRV8824 powered at 12V for the motor (DRV8824 trimpot adjusted). 
I am using a win10 laptop and an Arduino environment.
When using an Arduino mega2560 hooked to a RAMPS card with A DRV8824, I get correct motion of the motor using a StepperDriver library (with acceleration/deceleration capability)

I want now to use a and an ESP32_DEVKIT V4  WROOM , and my goal is to use 6 steppers at 200 steps/turn, to rotate concurently each with an eventual different speed in the range 20RPM-800RPM

I have started to test only one motor; I am encountering problems;  and would be happy to find a way to fix the problem:
I am using the "StepperDemo" from  FastAccelStepper
I have used GPIO5 for stepping, GPIO27 for enable (enable_low_active), GPIO32 for direction; also I have hooked up a led in series with  a 200 ohm resistance between pin GPIO5 and ground, so as to monitor step activity. 

Here is what I get on the console:

issue_title: Error message for unsupported languages
Set a label after  \printbibliography
issue_body:
For the use case etc. see https://tex.stackexchange.com/q/558982/98645

TL;DR is: I would like to have a `\label` after/for the heading set by biblatex when it generates the bibliography, so I can refer to that.

It's best practice in LaTeX to have labels for all that headings, so I guess this should be done here too.

It may be adjustable with an option for `\printbibliography`.

issue_title: Document the extended name format
issue_body: As suggested by @u-fischer in https://chat.stackexchange.com/transcript/message/55331517#55331517, we probably should have some more examples for the extended name format also in the `biblatex` doc: That makes it easier to find

issue_title: Compilation hangs when using volcite with pagenumber
issue_body:
When I try to compile a document (lets say it has the filename `main.tex`) that uses `\volcite` with a pagenumber (e.g. `\volcite{2}[33]{test}` I first run `lualatex main`, then `biber main` and after that `lualatex main` which then hangs. This problem occurs since version 3.15 (and also with 3.15, but I could successful compile the MWE down below using biblatex version 3.14). The problem also does not occur if I don't provide a page number (`\volcite{2}{test}`) Here is an MWE: `main.tex`: ```latex \documentclass{scrartcl} \usepackage{biblatex} \bibliography{bibliography} \begin{document} \volcite{1}[11]{name20} \printbibliography \end{document} ``` `bibliography.bib`: ``` @Book{name20, author = {Name, Vorname}, title = {Irgendein Titel}, publisher = {Beispiel-Verlag}, year = 2020} ```

issue_title: Break line first call of \text<lang> or \foreignlanguage

issue_title: Biblatex 3.15a \MakeSentenceCase* issue with relatedtype bytranslator
Biblatex 3.15a, casechanger=expl3, and latin1 encoding
Loading isodate after biblatex causes MakeSentenceCase* to misbehave
issue_body:
In v3.15a, loading the isodate package after biblatex means MakeSentenceCase* only makes a correct calculation about whether the current language is in the DeclareCaseLangs list if the language of a given entry is explicitly specified with `langid`.

MWE:

```latex
\documentclass[varwidth=67ex]{standalone}
\usepackage[british]{babel}
\usepackage{biblatex}
\addbibresource{biblatex-examples.bib}
\DeclareFieldFormat{titlecase}{\MakeSentenceCase*{#1}}
\usepackage[british,cleanlook]{isodate}

\begin{document}
Literal language british: \ifcaselang[british]{True}{False}.\\
\verb|\currentlang| \currentlang: \ifcaselang[\currentlang]{True}{False}.\\
\verb|\blx@languagename| \makeatletter\blx@languagename: \ifcaselang[\blx@languagename]{True}{False}.\makeatother\\
Implicit \verb|\currentlang|: \ifcaselang{True}{False}.\\

\MakeSentenceCase*{In Sentence Case} \cite{shore}.

\printbibliography
\end{document}
```

(The `shore` reference has Title Case in the bib file but no `langid` set.)

Expected output:

```markdown
Literal language british: True.
\currentlang british: True.
\blx@languagename british: True.
Implicit \currentlang: True.
In sentence case [1].

**References**

[1] Bradd Shore. “Twice-born, once conceived. Meaning construc-
tion and cultural cognition”. In: *American anthropologist.* New
ser. 93.1 (Mar. 1991), pp. 9–27.
```

I have done some testing with different versions; in all cases `\ifcaselang[british]` comes out True.

v3.15a - isodate before biblatex:

- Other `\ifcaselang` tests come out True
- `\MakeSentenceCase*` works as expected
- Titles in bibliography print as expected

v3.15a - isodate after biblatex:

- Other `\ifcaselang` tests come out False
- `\MakeSentenceCase*` does not change case
- Titles in bibliography print in Title Case

v3.14 - isodate before biblatex:

- Other `\ifcaselang` tests come out True
- `\MakeSentenceCase*` works as expected
- Titles in bibliography print as expected

v3.14 - isodate after biblatex:

- Other `\ifcaselang` tests come out False
- `\MakeSentenceCase*` works as expected
- Titles in bibliography print as expected

v3.13a - isodate before biblatex:

- Other `\ifcaselang` tests come out False
- `\MakeSentenceCase*` works as expected
- Titles in bibliography print as expected

v3.13a - isodate after biblatex:

- Other `\ifcaselang` tests come out False
- `\MakeSentenceCase*` works as expected
- Titles in bibliography print as expected

The results are the same regardless of whether expl3 or latex2e syntax is used.

I am not sure what it is about isodate that clobbers the more recent definitions of `ifcaselang`, so if avoiding the clash is not desirable, should there be a note in the documentation about the incompatibility?

issue_body:
При создании материалов можно случайно добавить текстуру окружения, вместо обычной текстуры. В 3д окне текстура будет отображаться и пользователь не заметит разницы между enviroment текстурой и обычной текстурой. Если материал имеет текстуру окружения, то экспорт будет работать некорректно. В xray материал попадёт пустая строка, вместо имени изображения. Нужно сохранять путь к текстуре, даже если материал использует enviroment текстуру. И нужно выдавать предупреждения, что в материале указаны неправильные ноды текстуры.

Вот пример:
[enviroment_texture_bug.zip](https://github.com/PavelBlend/blender-xray/files/5760271/enviroment_texture_bug.zip)

Если экспортировать объект Cube в object, то в сдк текстуры не будет.

issue_title: 多实例下的server每晚定时清理日志时可能会并发问题
issue_body:
**错误日志**
```
[GridFsManager] deleted log#5fe242297211c2739d327b1e failed.

com.mongodb.MongoGridFSException: No file found with the id: BsonObjectId{value=5fe242297211c2739d327b1e}
	at com.mongodb.client.gridfs.GridFSBucketImpl.executeDelete(GridFSBucketImpl.java:403)
	at com.mongodb.client.gridfs.GridFSBucketImpl.delete(GridFSBucketImpl.java:378)
	at com.mongodb.client.gridfs.GridFSBucketImpl.delete(GridFSBucketImpl.java:373)
```

我看了一下代码发现这个`CleanService`里面有一个spring的定时器`@Scheduled(cron = CLEAN_TIME_EXPRESSION)`然后报错由于以下语句导致的
```
        // 删除 GridFS 过期文件
        cleanRemote(GridFsManager.LOG_BUCKET, instanceInfoRetentionDay);
        cleanRemote(GridFsManager.CONTAINER_BUCKET, remoteContainerRetentionDay);
```
有一个地方想不明白，由于我们是部署了多个server端，假如直接用`Spring`的`Scheduled`那每一个server端凌晨3点时都会执行mongodb的操作，那当一条记录同时被两个server端查出来，但是第一个server端已经把这条记录删除，第二个server端再去删这条记录时就会报上面这个错误。不知道我理解的对不对？假如我理解不正确的地方麻烦指出一下，谢谢了:smile:

**Environment**
 - PowerJob Version: [e.g. 3.4.1]
 - Java Version: [e.g. OpenJDK 11]
 - OS: [e.g. CentOS 8.1]

issue_title: Profileモデルのデフォルト値設定
issue_body:
## 概要

ユーザー新規登録時の処理としてProfileモデルを同時に作成するが、デフォルト値を設定していないためデータベースにnullが格納されており、フロントエンドにAPIを送る際にnull valueを設定してしまうとフロントでの制御が複雑になる。そのためProfile modelにデフォルト値を設定した。

## 変更点
---

- [x] profile modelのmigrationファイル変更
  -  デフォルト値をそれぞれ telephone: "", major_category: 0 に設定
- [x] user_controllerにおいて、profile save前にcompany_site: ""のデフォルト値を設定し、バリデーションをスキップする

## 課題
---

- [ ] DBのtext型に対するデフォルト値の設定方法を検討 
    -  データベースと同様、textデータ型に対してはデフォルト値を設定できない(https://qiita.com/eduidl/items/ccb97284db79ad7e14c0)ため、 migrationファイルにおいてtext型にdefault変数を利用できない。そのためURLが保存されるcompany_siteはコントローラーにおいてProfileモデル生成時にデフォルト値を自動設定するように修正。デフォルト値を利用できるstring型も検討したが、URLは255文字制約を満たすとは限らないためtext型で進める方針。
    - Profileモデル生成時にバリデーションをスキップした。理由は、デフォルト値が設定されているため初期値でsaveしようとするとバリデーションの制約にかかるから。

## 参照
---

- [ActiveRecordでバリデーションを無視してデータを保存する方法](https://qiita.com/jagio/items/22cd7be7a052d20c409c)
- [migrationファイルreset時のエラー](https://blog.freedom-man.com/no-environment-in-schema-error)
- [Rails, MySQLでnot null制約のついたtext型のカラムを追加する](https://qiita.com/eduidl/items/ccb97284db79ad7e14c0)

## 備考
---

- データベースのデフォルト値を設定するために一度ロールバックを行いファイルに追記。開発初期段階であるため直接編集した。

* データベースリセット方法(https://qiita.com/s_tatsuki/items/3e1f119c91e21b8f0c33)
```
# numberに遡るmigration数を記載
rails db:rollback STEP=number

# migrationを確認
rails db:migrate:status

# migrationを再度実行
rails db:migrate
```

issue_title: Ansage nach Uhrzeit auswählbar
issue_body:
Mit meiner Frau ist gerade eine Diskussion entbrannt bzgl. der Sprachansage. Konkret geht u.a. um die Waschmaschine. Sie hätte gerne die Möglichkeit, das man eine Uhrzeit einstellen kann, wann die Sprachansage (nochmal) ausgegeben werden soll (z.B. als letzte Erinnerung des Tages wenn man am Abendbrot Tisch sitzt (18:30 Uhr o.ä.). 

Ihre Begründung, wenn Sie nicht zu Hause ist und die Ansage kommt, dann hört Sie es nicht und vergisst es dann doch wieder das die Maschine fertig ist.
Die Sprachansage kommt ja dann, wenn die eingestellten Lastparameter erreicht sind. Man kann zwar das TimeOut einstellen, aber das bezieht sich ja auf die Abschaltung.
Hier geht es auch nicht ums abschalten der Maschine, das will sie gar nicht (wegen Knitterschutz) Sie will einfach zu einer bestimmten Zeit daran erinnert werden, das noch was in der Maschine drin ist. 

Des weiteren will sie, das nur bestimmte Sprachansagen nur auf bestimmten Alexas ausgegeben werden.

Beispiel: Waschmaschine und Wäschetrockner sollen nur in der Küche, Stube und Schlafzimmer ausgegeben werden. Der Geschirrspüler ist ihr aber egal und da will sie KEINE Ansage im Schlafzimmer, sondern nur auf den Toiletten und im Bastelkeller haben. Schlafzimmer muss aber verknüpft sein, weil es sonst die Ansagen für Waschmaschine & Wäschetrockner nicht gäbe. Geschirrspüler muss ebenfalls definiert sein, weil sonst die anderen Räume nicht erreicht würden.

Also eine Zwickmühle bzgl. ihrer Vorstellungen ;)

issue_title: Detailed VF/AC kick messages
issue_body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
People are mostly frustrated when they get kicked because of a non-allowed-program-running (like  VF#33 Server blocks cFosSpeed / LAN manager NetLimit)

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Most of the people already know what program causes it and they're able to close it, but when someone who doesn't comes and asks what the issue is, we have to ask for an MTA Diag log and hand-pick the program causing it. It would be nice if MTA could log the exact process name & process install location to its report.log. Maybe it could also show what process is causing the issue to the end-user as well.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
1) MTA Client could offer to terminate these processes and wait for user input to allow or disallow it
2) A more detailed error output could be used with instructions on how to end the process. I don't think this is possible considering how small the error popup window is.
3) More clear wording could be used in the error message. This user got 3 program names (cFosSpeed, LAN manager and NetLimiter) but it was only MSI_Gaming_Lan_Manager.exe

**Additional context**
confused players asking for help on Discord:
https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/675939577281773568/794933803231084574/20210102_172248.jpg

case about this guy: he probably had a virus and it has installed a iqvw64e.sys on his system. when you Google what iqvw64e.sys is, you get this result: https://www.file.net/process/iqvw64e.sys.html
guy not only had this program installed, he also didn't have anything related to this program in its system32 folder. turns out, this file was located in C:\Users\username\AppData\Local\Temp\. I had to contact Dutchman to help me figure out where it was installed. I doubt if any end-user knows this file path exists.
There were 3 others that asked for help about this file, if we had its location reported in report.log or somewhere else, I wouldn't have had to disturb Dutchman about it and could've just solved the issue myself.
https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/675939577281773568/794279208141979678/unknown.png

[Bug] MsBuildTask does not set GitVersionInformation.UncommittedChanges
issue_body:
**Describe the bug**
I have added the GitVersionTask (5.5.1) nuget package to a C# command line application.  Within that application I test the **UncommitedChanges** variable to see if the code was built from "dirty" source (i.e. code with changes that were not committed first).
 
` var dirtyBuild =  GitVersionInformation.UncommittedChanges != "0";`

I am *expecting* this variable to hold some measure of the extent of locally modified files (# diff lines, # modified files etc) but it seems to return **"0"** regardless of whether I have made local changes to the source prior to the build.  For example here is the output of git diff prior to build...

```
16:03>git diff --stat
 Test/Test.cs | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
```
After building this source,  `Console.WriteLine(GitVersionInformation.UncommittedChanges);` displays "0";

Note that other **GitVersionInformation** fields such as **ShortSha**, **CommitDate** etc are populated as expected so the task is running correctly.


## Possible Fix
<!-- Not obligatory, but suggest a fix or reason for the bug -->

## Steps to Reproduce
- Create a new C# Console Application in Visual Studio
- Add the GitVersionTask nuget package to the application
- Ensure the project is added to source control
- Add   `Console.WriteLine(GitVersionInformation.UncommittedChanges); ` to the main method
- Build and run the application

Visual Studio Preview 16.9.0 pv2
Windows 10

issue_title: Integration with poetry's pyproject.toml
issue_body:
There is something I want to achieve but I am unsure as to what is the best approach. I was suggested on Gitter to post my usecase here in the hope of coming up with an example solution.

I have a current 100% Python project that is managed using [poetry](https://python-poetry.org/). It uses a `pyproject.toml` file to manage the project's dependencies.

Also, this project is deployed to an internal pypy repository using `poetry publish --repository internalpypy` as a wheel that gets pulled down by other projects (themselves using poetry too).

I would like to port one function of the Python project to Rust since it is quite heavy. I want to minimize changes to the project's organization. As such, how can I introduce the rust code to be built and included in the final wheel using only `poetry build` (and `poetry publish`)?

I did worked previously with [`milksnake`](https://github.com/getsentry/milksnake) but unfortunately:
* it doesn't support poetry (it requires a `setup.py` file to be configured properly but poetry's `pyproject.toml` replaces the `setup.py` file).
* it is abandoned

I checked [`maturin`](https://github.com/PyO3/maturin) but:
* it seems to expect a specific directory structure which would be too disruptive for my project
* it seems to only build a 100% Rust wheel. This means that for a mixed rust-python project the main project would need to be split into two, introducing extra release complications.

Some poetry related issues I've found when searching this:
* Add support for non pure python projects: https://github.com/python-poetry/poetry/issues/11
* Allow optional compilation of C extensions: https://github.com/python-poetry/poetry/issues/2330

I am looking at [`setuptools-rust`](https://github.com/PyO3/setuptools-rust) right now.

Thanks!

issue_title: Question: Overriding Identifiable.Id Property leads to error
issue_body:
Hey there, since I'm new to this framework, this is more a question than a bug... Is this behaviour intended or am I missing something?


#### DESCRIPTION

Overriding `Identifiable.Id Property` leads to error `Sequence contains more than one matching element`, because of `resourceContext.Attributes.Single` in https://github.com/json-api-dotnet/JsonApiDotNetCore/blob/e63ddf145aee9897c124c5b7c37aac973c737a52/src/JsonApiDotNetCore/Queries/Internal/QueryLayerComposer.cs#L444

#### STEPS TO REPRODUCE

Using a basic `AbstractModel` extending `Identifiable` to use the `[DatabaseGenerated(DatabaseGeneratedOption.Identity)]` 
```c#
    public abstract class AbstractModel : Identifiable<Guid>
    {
        [Key]
        [DatabaseGenerated(DatabaseGeneratedOption.Identity)]
        public new Guid Id { get; set; }
        [Attr] public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; } = DateTime.MinValue;
        [Attr] public DateTime UpdatedDate { get; set; } = DateTime.MinValue;
    }
```

Then use a non-abstract model extending this one.

#### EXPECTED BEHAVIOR

It uses the correct Id field of the `AbstractModel`

#### ACTUAL BEHAVIOR

Error `Sequence contains more than one matching element`.

#### VERSIONS USED
- JsonApiDotNetCore version: 4.0.0
- ASP.NET Core version: 3.1.102
- Entity Framework Core version: 5.0.0
- Database provider: sqlite

**Describe the bug**
I exported my Goodreads library while I was still reading some books but didn't import them into Bookwyrm until after I had finished them (and marked them as read in Bookwyrm). Server Error

1. Mark a book as currently reading in Goodreads

6. Attempt to move book back to "Read"

**Expected behavior**
I would expect a book to stay marked as read even if it was marked as "Currently Reading" in an import if the "Finished Reading" date in Bookwyrm was later than the "Started/Shelved" date in the import

issue_title: Allow search for non-"karaoke" results
issue_body:
The search method forces "karaoke" at the end of the search string to return karaoke results. This works most of the time, but may be too limiting, as some karaoke results could show under "lyrics" "instrumental" or "raw". We should allow some way to disable the "karaoke" string and just allow a basic plain text search. 

Perhaps a checkbox under the search input "include non-karaoke matches" and a new search mode, like an optional parameter on the search method karaokeOnly=true.

issue_title: Predicate call site specific mutations
issue_body:
Rubies convention of postfixing predicate methods with an `?` should allow to add predicate call site specific mutations.
- Replace call site with `true` (already included in other mutation operators)
- Replace call site with `false` (currently not included, we emit `nil` already, an explicit `false` will cover more semantics`).

issue_title: Plastic centroid/principal axis centroid not at elastic centroid for doubly symmetric section
issue_body:
**Describe the bug**
In the following code I would expect the plastic centroid to be at the origin (0, 0) and align with the elastic centroid. Yet it is reporting the plastic centroid below the origin. Section geometry centroid is shifted to 0,0 position.

Also, the horizontal principal axis is shown correctly at y=0, but the principal plastic axis centroid is not, being drawn below y=0.

The reported results agree with the plot in so far as the plastic centroid is not at 0,0 point.

Is this possibly a bug or maybe I'm missing something obvious here?

**To Reproduce**
Run code below and observe results

```
import sectionproperties.pre.sections as sections
from sectionproperties.analysis.cross_section import CrossSection

mesh_area = 25  # max mesh size

d = 612  # I section depth
b_f = 229  # I-section flange width
t_f = 19.6  # I-section flange thickness
t_w = 11.9  # I-section web thickness
r_1 = 14  # I-section root radii
n_r = 50  # number of points considered around root radii

d_p = 650  # strengthening plate depth
b_p = 12  # strengthening plate thickness

# create constituent geometry
geometry1 = sections.ISection(d=d, b=b_f, t_f=t_f, t_w=t_w, r=r_1, n_r=n_r, shift=[-b_f / 2, -d / 2])
geometry2 = sections.RectangularSection(d=d_p, b=b_p, shift=[-b_f / 2 - b_p, -d_p / 2])
geometry3 = sections.RectangularSection(d=d_p, b=b_p, shift=[b_f / 2, -d_p / 2])

# create merged section
geometry = sections.MergedSection([geometry1, geometry2, geometry3])

# add holes
geometry.add_hole([-b_f / 2, 0])
geometry.add_hole([b_f / 2, 0])

# create mesh
mesh = geometry.create_mesh(mesh_sizes=[mesh_area, mesh_area, mesh_area])

# clean geometry
geometry.clean_geometry(verbose=True)

# create section
section = CrossSection(geometry, mesh)

# calculate results
section.calculate_geometric_properties()
section.calculate_plastic_properties()
section.calculate_warping_properties()

# plot results
section.plot_mesh()
section.plot_centroids()

# display all results
# check https://sectionproperties.readthedocs.io/en/latest/rst/post.html for definitions
section.display_results(fmt='.3f')

# this will specifically display torsion and warping constants
J = section.get_j()
I_w = section.get_gamma()
print(f'J = {J}')
print(f'I_w = {I_w}')
```


**Expected behaviour**
For doubly symmetric section plastic and elastic centroid should align?

**Screenshots**
Note how principal plastic axis centroid does not align with the principal axes, and plastic centroid is shown below elastic centroid:-
![Figure_1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36808164/102696973-213be380-4297-11eb-8929-8b7dfa4553bf.png)


**Additional context**
Using latest version 1.0.7

This would be a more useful and flexible package if the method send_email() could do the following things:
- [x] Take in a list of emails instead of presetting them in the script itself
- [x] Dynamically receive different types of emails. One possibility would be to have send_email() take in an argument called `lines` which is a list where each item is one line in the email. This seems simpler than passing variables through the `eMessages` class.

issue_title: Update emailer.py to handle one vs. multiple recipient email addresses
issue_body:
Right now the [script](https://github.com/mr-devs/my-NaN-scripts/blob/main/emailer.py) successfully sends emails to a list of email addresses defined in line 102.

```python
destEmail = ["mdeverna@iu.edu", "mdeverna2790@gmail.com"]
```

the problem is that if we only enter one email address in this list, or replace this list with a single email address in the form of a string, it will break on line 124

```python
msg['To'] = ",".join(destEmail)
```

A simple if-statement checking for the length of the provided list (or whether it is simply a string) and then not using the ",".join(destEmail) method will fix this problem.

issue_title: Build Film List Page
Socket to remote server never explicitly closed
issue_body:
Please call me stupid, but I fail to see where the TCP socket is closed. `main()` has
https://github.com/johnmehr/gitup/blob/4463ee04e02298f99b83b086c858f1b3293861bd/gitup.c#L2340-L2344
but I fail to see a `close(connection.socket_descriptor)`.  `SSL_shutdown()` only terminates the TLS session with a `close_notify`, but does not close the underlying socket. This may lead to a broken socket on the peer's side.

I'd be happy to be proved wrong.

issue_title: "." not supported in annotation variables (Annotation Sets)
issue_body: Collections such as File, Cohort, Individual, Family and Sample support Annotation Sets. This is really useful to store and query for user-defined fields that have not been considered as part of the built-in data model OpenCGA provides. Although this feature works great, we have discovered that "." are not supported as part of a variable field. We will fix this issue and support any possible character.

issue_title: Bug: Multiple attendances for waitinglisted members
issue_body:
## Description of the issue 📄
As a member can either:
- join multiple waiting lists for workshops taking place on the same day
- join a workshop and the waiting list of another workshop taking place on the same day

When allocating waiting list positions, do not allow members who are already attending a workshop on that day to be added.

This could happen:
1. when an existing attendance updates their RSVP to not attending
2. when an admin attempts to move someone from the waiting list to the workshop

Checks and tests verifying this behavior should be implemented for both of the above mentioned bits of funtionality.

(This issue is specifically for workshops as adding checks for other events has a bit more complexity so it should be tackled separately)

issue_title: Specify different roles
issue_body:
Currently in the codebar app we have 2 different roles, admin and organiser. This has become too simple and we need to be able to grant granular roles. 

- **Chapter organisers** should be able to create sponsors and set up workshops
- **Event organisers** should be able to create sponsors and set up events
- **Monthly organisers** should be able to create sponsors and set up monthly events

One person should be able to have multiple roles if they're involved in multiple codebar things.

- **Admins** should still be able to do everything

issue_title: force_sort_within_sections is not case-insensitive
issue_body:
I want my from-imports and straight-imports to be sorted together so I'd like to use `--force-sort-within-sections`. And I want my modules to be sorted case-insensitively too, which is already the default.

Sort the following with the `--force-sort-within-sections` flag:

    import a
    from Z import b, C

With a bash command that's: `echo -e 'import a\nfrom Z import b, C' | isort - --force-sort-within-sections`

### Expected result

    import a
    from Z import C, b

### Actual result

    from Z import C, b
    import a

The [`sorting.section_key`](https://github.com/PyCQA/isort/blob/8e6d383064d337813a5b021bd597e166ccd630b3/isort/sorting.py#L54) function that gets called doesn't care about the `case_sensitive` setting. It _does_ however get `order_by_type` passed in as a parameter and that lowercases the line if it's turned off. So if I call it like this: 

    echo -e 'import a\nfrom Z import b, C' | isort - --force-sort-within-sections --dont-order-by-type

I get:

    import a
    from Z import b, C

But that's still not what I want, because I _do_ want to order by type.

I see the `order_by_type` was added in 1372970. And I also see there's already a unit test covering this: https://github.com/PyCQA/isort/blob/6e5414cb72ee822d351968626bb9a37e10425857/tests/unit/test_isort.py#L2358

Is this a deliberate choice or an oversight? Should there be some code in there that lowercases just the module names (depending on `case_sensitive`)? And should `order_by_type` only lowercase the imported names, so it doesn't affect the module order?

issue_title: With -update flag, if a single test fails all autogold files will be removed
Custom Alias config for NBT items
issue_body:
#### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.
It can be a pain to figure out what book or sword or potion (items with custom nbt data) is being sold. While Potion#97 makes sense to the game, that could be anything to a player.


#### Describe the solution you'd like
Add a custom alias config for things like books, maps, potions, basically anything that uses nbt tags.

Potion#97 would become "Luck Potion":

```
custom_alias_1:
  item: 'Potion#97'
  alias: 'Luck Potion'
```

 Adding aliases to the config could be left to a permissions node, or simply editing and reloading the yml file manually. Loading a file with a conflicting alias (where 'Potion#97' is given the name 'Diamond', for example) would just default to the unmodified alias system to avoid conflicts/player scams.


#### Describe alternatives you've considered
I've looked at other plugins, but CS is too elegant to get rid of. 


#### Additional context
Would be willing to donate some $ to get this feature added.

issue_title: Okta authorization_code flow not working
issue_body:
## Expected Behavior

I have oauth2_proxy v6.1.1 configured in my kubernetes cluster and I'm trying to make the authorization code flow to work.
But looks like the /token endpoint (redeem) is not being requested

## Current Behavior

- When I request the gateway address, I get redirected to the proxy 
- Then the proxy redirects me to the Okta login page.
- Once logged in, I'm redirected back to the proxy with the `&code=<authz_code>` appended to the URL.
- Then the proxy redirects to the upstream service. **At this point I expect it to make a request to Okta to exchange the authz code for and Access Token.**

## Possible Solution

Maybe I am missing some configuration

## Steps to Reproduce (for bugs)

Here is the args I'm currently using
```yaml
      containers:
      - name: oauth2-proxy
        image: quay.io/oauth2-proxy/oauth2-proxy:v6.1.1
        args:
        - --provider=oidc
        - --cookie-secure=true
        - --cookie-samesite=lax
        - --cookie-refresh=1h
        - --cookie-expire=4h
        - --cookie-name=_oauth2_proxy_istio_ingressgateway
        - --set-authorization-header=true
        - --pass-authorization-header=true
        - --pass-access-token=true
        - --email-domain=*
        - --http-address=0.0.0.0:4180
        - --upstream=static://200
        - --skip-provider-button=true
        - --whitelist-domain=envoy-local.com
        - --oidc-issuer-url=https://test.okta.com/oauth2/<id>
        - --request-logging=true

issue_title: Epic: Library Support - Library Entities
issue_body:
A Library entity represents a ICollection of Series. A Library is bound to one of more physical folders on the disk that contain a given metadata type. 

First pass implementation for a Library is:
Name,
Metadata Type (Manga, Comic, Book, Raw)
Folders
Thumb Image (image to show on the UI)


First pass implementation should only focus on MetadataType.Manga.

The following APIs are needed with DTO, Entities, and Migrations:
- [x] GetLibraries
- [ ] GetLibrary(int libraryId)
- [ ] UpdateLibrary (update properties of it)
- [ ] DeleteLibrary
- [x] CreateLibrary

N.B. Use Optimistic Concurency with EF (RowVersion) as libraries might be updated at same time and we need to prevent locking.

issue_title: enable 3 service nodes
issue_body:
So far we only have one service node, which means when service is redeploying, it will not be available for a while.

Enable 3 nodes will mitigate this situation, and also avoid single point failure issue.

issue_title: Japanese MRA has wrong checksums

It probably works ok if your rom  is un-merged? For maximum split/merged/unmerged compatibility the checksums should be updated and the zip attribute changed to "dodonpach.zip|dodonpachj.zip"

issue_title: Group headers are offset by the Header components height using GroupedVirtuoso
issue_body:
Happy new year 🎊 and thanks for creating this wonderful library!

I'm just starting to play around with it now and loving it so far.

issue_title: [BUG] Asking for printer configuration on an ESP3D-flashed SonOff turns the SonOff off
issue_body:
In "Smoothieware target" mode, with ESP3D running on a Sonoff device that controls the power of the 3D printer, asking for the printer configuration turns the printer off, making the configuration data useless (it cannot be saved onto the printer).

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1.  Turn the Sonoff ON using [ESP201]P12 V1
2. Click on ESP3D "Printer tab"
3. Clink on the Printer configuration "button"
4. The printer turns off (the configuration cannot be saved)

**Expected behavior**
Asking for the printer configuration should not change the GPIOs (especially GPIO 12).

**ESP3D Firmware:**
No firmware change, the issue has been there for quite a time.
SDK: 2.2.1(cfd48f3)
FW version: 2.1.1.b7 ESP8266/8586
WebUI version: 2.1b68

 - Smoothieware

issue_title: ChunkRender sometimes does not update tiles
issue_body:
When breaking a block causes tiles to disappear, the chunk may sometimes decide to not remove deleted tiles from the model. The next model update fixes everything.

*Steps to reproduce*
Enter a world, start breaking grass blocks. At some point you will see floating grass tiles that should have been removed. Break another (unrelated) block and observe the tiles disappear. The issue seems to trigger randomly and quite rarely; perhaps once every twenty blocks or so.

This is probably related to lack of synchronization in `ChunkRender`.

issue_title: Build a Product Landing Page
issue_body:
Objective: Build a CodePen.io app that is functionally similar to this: https://codepen.io/freeCodeCamp/full/RKRbwL.

Fulfill the below user stories and get all of the tests to pass. Give it your own personal style.

You can use HTML, JavaScript, and CSS to complete this project. Plain CSS is recommended because that is what the lessons have covered so far and you should get some practice with plain CSS. You can use Bootstrap or SASS if you choose. Additional technologies (just for example jQuery, React, Angular, or Vue) are not recommended for this project, and using them is at your own risk. Other projects will give you a chance to work with different technology stacks like React. We will accept and try to fix all issue reports that use the suggested technology stack for this project. Happy coding!

User Story #1: My product landing page should have a header element with a corresponding id="header".

User Story #2: I can see an image within the header element with a corresponding id="header-img". A company logo would make a good image here.

User Story #3: Within the #header element I can see a nav element with a corresponding id="nav-bar".

User Story #4: I can see at least three clickable elements inside the nav element, each with the class nav-link.

User Story #5: When I click a .nav-link button in the nav element, I am taken to the corresponding section of the landing page.

User Story #6: I can watch an embedded product video with id="video".

User Story #7: My landing page has a form element with a corresponding id="form".

User Story #8: Within the form, there is an input field with id="email" where I can enter an email address.

User Story #9: The #email input field should have placeholder text to let the user know what the field is for.

User Story #10: The #email input field uses HTML5 validation to confirm that the entered text is an email address.

User Story #11: Within the form, there is a submit input with a corresponding id="submit".

User Story #12: When I click the #submit element, the email is submitted to a static page (use this mock URL: https://www.freecodecamp.com/email-submit).

User Story #13: The navbar should always be at the top of the viewport.

User Story #14: My product landing page should have at least one media query.

User Story #15: My product landing page should utilize CSS flexbox at least once.

You can build your project by forking this CodePen pen. Or you can use this CDN link to run the tests in any environment you like: https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/testable-projects-fcc/v1/bundle.js

issue_title: [09/01/21] RF-15 Verifica Appuntamenti
Getting Started with GitHub
issue_body:
# :wave: Welcome to GitHub Learning Lab's "Introduction to GitHub" To get started, I’ll guide you through some important first steps in coding and collaborating on GitHub. :point_down: _This arrow means you can expand the window! Click on them throughout the course to find more information._
What is GitHub?
## What is GitHub? I'm glad you asked! Many people come to GitHub because they want to contribute to open source [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#open-source) projects, or they're invited by teammates or classmates who use it for their projects. Why do people use GitHub for these projects? **At its heart, GitHub is a collaboration platform.** From software to legal documents, you can count on GitHub to help you do your best work with the collaboration and security tools your team needs. With GitHub, you can keep projects completely private, invite the world to collaborate, and streamline every step of your project. **GitHub is also a powerful version control tool.** GitHub uses Git [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#git), the most popular open source version control software, to track every contribution and contributor [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#contributor) to your project--so you know exactly where every line of code came from. **GitHub helps people do much more.** GitHub is used to build some of the most advanced technologies in the world. Whether you're visualizing data or building a new game, there's a whole community and set of tools on GitHub that can get you to the next step. This course starts with the basics, but we'll dig into the rest later! :tv: [Video: What is GitHub?](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w3jLJU7DT5E)

Exploring a GitHub repository
## Exploring a GitHub repository :tv: [Video: Exploring a repository](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R8OAwrcMlRw) ### More features The video covered some of the most commonly-used features. Here are a few other items you can find in GitHub repositories: - Project boards: Create Kanban-style task tracking board within GitHub - Wiki: Create and store relevant project documentation - Insights: View a drop-down menu that contains links to analytics tools for your repository including: - Pulse: Find information about the work that has been completed and the work that’s in-progress in this project dashboard - Graphs: Graphs provide a more granular view of the repository activity including who contributed to the repository, who forked it, and when they completed the work ### Special Files In the video you learned about a special file called the README.md. Here are a few other special files you can add to your repositories: - CONTRIBUTING.md: The `CONTRIBUTING.md` is used to describe the process for contributing to the repository. A link to the `CONTRIBUTING.md` file is shown anytime someone creates a new issue or pull request. - ISSUE_TEMPLATE.md: The `ISSUE_TEMPLATE.md` is another file you can use to pre-populate the body of an issue. For example, if you always need the same types of information for bug reports, include it in the issue template, and every new issue will be opened with your recommended starter text.
### Using issues This is an issue [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#issue): a place where you can have conversations about bugs in your code, code review, and just about anything else. Issue titles are like email subject lines. They tell your collaborators what the issue is about at a glance. For example, the title of this issue is Getting Started with GitHub.
Using GitHub Issues ## Using GitHub issues Issues are used to discuss ideas, enhancements, tasks, and bugs. They make collaboration easier by: - Providing everyone (even future team members) with the complete story in one place - Allowing you to cross-link to other issues and pull requests [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#pull-request) - Creating a single, comprehensive record of how and why you made certain decisions - Allowing you to easily pull the right people and teams into a conversation with @-mentions :tv: [Video: Using issues](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zhj46r5D0nQ)
Managing notifications
## Managing notifications :tv: [Video: Watching, notifications, stars, and explore](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ocQldxF7fMY) Once you've commented on an issue or pull request, you'll start receiving email notifications when there's activity in the thread. ### How to silence or unmute specific conversations 1. Go to the issue or pull request 2. Under _"Notifications"_, click the **Unsubscribe** button on the right to silence notifications or **Subscribe** to unmute them You'll see a short description that explains your current notification status. ### How to customize notifications in Settings 1. Click your profile icon 2. Click **Settings** 3. Click **Notifications** from the menu on the left and [adjust your notification preferences](https://help.github.com/articles/managing-notification-delivery-methods/) ### Repository notification options * **Watch**: You'll receive a notification when a new issue, pull request or comment is posted, and when an issue is closed or a pull request is merged * **Not watching**: You'll no longer receive notifications unless you're @-mentioned * **Ignore**: You'll no longer receive any notifications from the repository ### How to review notifications for the repositories you're watching 1. Click your profile icon 2. Click **Settings** 3. Click **Notification** from the menu on the left 4. Click on the [things you’re watching](https://github.com/watching) link 5. Select the **Watching** tab 6. Click the **Unwatch** button to disable notifications, or **Watch** to enable them

issue_title: Passwords can be stored in clear in database
issue_body:
# Security
Passwords are stored in clear in database

## Environment
- **Version**: 11.0

## Expected and actual behavior
The database has in table `llx_user` the column `pass` which contents password in clear. It has also `pass_crypted` which is fine
Passwords shouldn't be stored in clear, but only in encrypted form.
I have then enabled "Chiffrer les mots de passe stockés dans la base de données (PAS en texte brut).". Then passwords in column `pass` has been deleted.
I think that this has not to be an option and should be the default behaviour.

issue_title: Asynchronous background fetching causes confusing behavior if items are requested before they are done being fetched
issue_body:
Example code:

    client = PyKustoClient(CLUSTER)
    client.get_databases_names()

This might return an empty list because fetching the list of databases in the background did not finish yet. This is confusing for the user, who might think there are no databases, or that there is a bug in getting the list.

Possible solutions:

1. Print a log message to explain why the returned list is empty.
1. Make the various "get_" methods blocking.

issue_title: PHOTOPRISM_THUMB_UNCACHED still creates thumbs while indexing
issue_body:
Hi,

maybe I misunderstand the `PHOTOPRISM_THUMB_UNCACHED` from https://docs.photoprism.org/getting-started/config-options/ but I was under an impression that with that env variable (I'm running in Docker) it would prevent the thumbnails from being created while indexing the collection, and only on-demand when a collection is opened. 

I've also disabled the TensorFlow too with the hope to significantly speed up the process of indexing (only sizes, folder name and geo data to be extracted). I am running the app on my Synology NAS with really limited resources and I don't think I want all the thumbs of my 400k photo collection to be created, but rather selectively.

Maybe I just don't understand the config switch, but checking the code shows the actual flag is only checked when doing `GET` but not when reindexing (or I couldn't spot it)

Cheers

issue_title: Contract hourlyRate BigDecimal With No Decimals
issue_body:
The Contract hourly rate (for new contract or update contract) reaches the backend as ``double`` and then it is only divided by ``100``, but the resulting BigDecimal is not rounded. 

The BigDecimal should be rounded so that it has no decimals, since this value represents the lowest denomination, the cents.

issue_title: Global Configuration System
issue_body:
Right now there are a few places where we can optionally generate pretty-printed JSON and where we can register custom exporters and importers.  Instead of making all these static lists or parameters to functions, it'd be nicer to have a reified "configuration" system.  This would allow for more concisely tuning the overall behavior of Voorhees, while also providing an easy way to swap between multiple configurations (e.g. debug and release).

This would break down to:
- Create a `JsonConfig` class and a "current config" singleton.  The "current config" singleton is populated with a set of default configuration values.
- Move configuration options out of `JsonMapper` and `JsonReader` function parameters into `JsonConfig`, and update references.
- Document the config system, available options and swapping procedures.

It would be nice to have a "currency" option available for the TextField's "type" prop in react-md.

#### Features:
- Implemented as a "number" type such that the numeric keypad is used on mobile devices
- Add an optional "prefix" prop (typically "$" for a U.S. use case)
- Add an optional "suffix" prop ("USD", "GBP", etc)
- Inserts formatting commas as the user types (1,234,567.89)
  - Shifts formatting commas as the user edits the middle of the number

#### Optional Features:
- Format the field according to the browser locale
- Add an optional "locale" prop that will override browser locale
- Format the input to 2 (depending on locale) decimal places as part of the "onBlur" event
- Limit input characters depending on locale

issue_body:
It must be possible to specify a configuration IRI to configure behaviour.

The configuration IRI is specified manually by the user. The configuration IRI can be changed at any time by the user. Only one configuration IRI can be entered. If the configuration IRI is changed by the user, only this configuration is considered. The previous one is forgotten.

issue_title: Stylesheet input
issue_body:
It must be possible to specify a stylesheet IRI to configure visual style of the displayed knowledge graph.

The stylesheet IRI is specified manually by the user. The stylesheet IRI can be changed at any time by the user. Only one stylesheet IRI can be entered. If the stylesheet IRI is changed by the user, only this stylesheet is considered and reapplied to the whole knowledge graph. The previous one is forgotten.

issue_title: Resource input
issue_body:
It must be possible to specify a resource IRI which is then displayed in the visual area of the knowledge graph browser.

The resource IRI is specified manually by the user. There must be a "Show" button next to the input field for the resource IRI. After the user clicks on the button, the resource is displayed as a node in the visual area of the knowledge graph browser.

Displaying the resource means that the `preview` method is called on the server with the default view for the resource. The output is used to display the resource.

The user can change the resource IRI. Anytime the user clicks on the button, the specified resource is displayed. If the resource is already displayed it is not displayed again as a new node.

issue_title: Resource detail
issue_body:
When the user single-clicks on a node, a detail of the resource represented by the node is displayed in the resource detail area of the knowledge graph browser.

The data for the detail is loaded by calling the `detail` method on the server. The current view of the node is supplied as the `view` parameter.

The data for the detail loaded from the server is displayed as a two-columns table with the first column containing the name of a data property and the second column containing the value of the data property.

A property is displayed as link with the propety IRI.

There is also the full label of the node representing the resource displayed as a heading at the top of the detail area. It is a link with the resource IRI.

Further, the detail contains a list of all views for the resource. This list is loaded from the server by calling the `view-sets` method. The current view for the resource is highlighted. The user may change here the current view.

If no current view has been selected by the user for the resource yet, the default one is chosen as the current view.

Changing the current view does not affect the current views of other displayed resources.

issue_title: Resource context menu
issue_body: When the user single-clicks on a node representing a resource, a context menu is displayed at the node representing the resource. The context menu contains context actions for the node. These actions are defined by other issues.

issue_title: Resource hiding and showing
issue_body:
In the context menu of a resource, there is an action which hides a displayed node representing the resource. All edges associated with the resource are hidden as well.

In the main menu of the knowledge graph browser, there is an action which shows all hidden resources. The user may choose a hidden resource which shows the node representing the resource. 

There are also other possible ways to show again a hidden resource (e.g., #8 #9 ).

When a resource is is shown again its node displayed at the position where it has been when the resource was hidden.

issue_title: Resource expansion
issue_body:
When the user double-clicks on a node, the resource represented by the node is expanded.

The expansion of the resource is loaded by calling the `expand` method on the server. The current view of the node is supplied as the `view` parameter.

It is also possible to expand the node using the list of all views for the resource displayed in the detail of the resource (see #4). Next to each view in the list there is an expand button. When the users clicks on the expand button, the resource is expanded using the associated view. This view is set as the current view.

issue_title: Resource filtering by graph properties
issue_body:
Displayed resources can be filtered by various graph properties. More different graph properties will be considered in the future. For now, the following filters must be provided to the user:

- Show nodes with a degree in a given interval
- Show nodes with an incomming degree in a given interval
- Show nodes with an outgoing degree in a given interval

The nodes which are filtered out are hidden. Each hidden nodes behaves as described in #6 .

issue_title: Resource filtering by semantic properties
issue_body:
Displayed resources can be filtered by various semantic (data) properties.  More different semantic properties will be considered in the future. For now, the following filters must be provided to the user:
- Show nodes with given semantic types. All semantic types loaded from the server are displayed to define the filter. The user may select one or more types.

The nodes which are filtered out are hidden. Each hidden nodes behaves as described in #6 .

issue_title: Multilingual user interface
issue_body:
The user interface must be multilingual

1) All UI labels must be multilingual.

2) Visualized graph must be multilingual.

Currently, only EN is supported but we will add CS in the future.

For 2) we will add a language parameter to server requests later. The server will return strings in the requested language if available and in EN if not available. For now, work with the labels you get from the server.

For 1) make the UI code so that new languages can be added easilly without code modifications.

issue_title: Ticking Entities (Possible Incompatibilities with Scaling Health Mod)
issue_body:
Hi, I'm experiencing an issue with both Lost Trinkets and Scaling Health mod, Thanks to the owner of Guard Villagers, I'd reported this problem to the owner of that mod and they told me that what's causing the ticking entities is this mod.

Apparently whenever I have both Scaling Health and Lost Trinkets installed that ticking entities are appearing in my modded game and crashes my game. I had thought that both scaling health and guard villagers were the cause of this but now I'm thinking otherwise. 

Now I'm thinking that this problem has something to do with lost trinkets being hard-coded to minecraft's vanilla health system while scaling health slightly modifies the health system in some way that lost trinkets doesn't like that and causes ticking entities and eventually causing the game to crash cause some of your trinkets that messes around with the vanilla health system prefers to stick with the vanilla health system instead of what scaling health changes.

I already know that Lost Trinkets may not like First Aid mod either since First Aid mod changes the health system entirely by replacing it with First Aid's own health system which some of your trinkets will not like that change at all and certainly will cause the game to crash in some way or will make ticking entities to appear and cause the game to crash that way.

Btw my Minecraft version is 1.16.4, Forge version 35.1.28, mod versions for both lost trinkets and scaling health; Lost Trinkets: 0.1.5 | Scaling Health 4.0.1+1

issue_title: Djinni Machine Operator Erases Storage Actuator's Inventory
issue_body:
**Describe the bug**
When shift-right clicking a storage actuator or a stable wormhole with a Djinni Machine Operator's Book of Calling in Machine Settings mode, the Djinni will erase all the items in the storage inventory except for a single item, which will rapidly flicker in and out of its inventory. All other items in the storage will disappear. 

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Set up a storage actuator with 5 t2 stabilizers. Make sure at lest 3 types of items are in the storage. (I used nether quartz, cobblestone, and coal blocks). Or set up a stabilized wormhole connected to the above actuator
2. Create a bound djinni operator and have the operator in the world. 
3. Right click open air with the book
4. Set the mode to 'Machine Settings'
5. Hit the x button on the bottom to close the menu.
6. Shift right click the actuator (or a wormhole linked to the actuator) with the book.
7. The djinni will go over to the wormhole or actuator and delete all the items, leaving only a single itemstack in the storage that it will attempt to infinitely extract and insert/
**Expected behavior**

The Djinni should either not go to the actuator/wormhole and delete all the items.

issue_title: Getting Started with GitHub
issue_body:
# :wave: Welcome to GitHub Learning Lab's "Introduction to GitHub" To get started, I’ll guide you through some important first steps in coding and collaborating on GitHub. :point_down: _This arrow means you can expand the window! Click on them throughout the course to find more information._
What is GitHub?
## What is GitHub? I'm glad you asked! Many people come to GitHub because they want to contribute to open source [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#open-source) projects, or they're invited by teammates or classmates who use it for their projects. Why do people use GitHub for these projects? **At its heart, GitHub is a collaboration platform.** From software to legal documents, you can count on GitHub to help you do your best work with the collaboration and security tools your team needs. With GitHub, you can keep projects completely private, invite the world to collaborate, and streamline every step of your project. **GitHub is also a powerful version control tool.** GitHub uses Git [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#git), the most popular open source version control software, to track every contribution and contributor [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#contributor) to your project--so you know exactly where every line of code came from. **GitHub helps people do much more.** GitHub is used to build some of the most advanced technologies in the world. Whether you're visualizing data or building a new game, there's a whole community and set of tools on GitHub that can get you to the next step. This course starts with the basics, but we'll dig into the rest later! :tv: [Video: What is GitHub?](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w3jLJU7DT5E)

Exploring a GitHub repository
## Exploring a GitHub repository :tv: [Video: Exploring a repository](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R8OAwrcMlRw) ### More features The video covered some of the most commonly-used features. Here are a few other items you can find in GitHub repositories: - Project boards: Create Kanban-style task tracking board within GitHub - Wiki: Create and store relevant project documentation - Insights: View a drop-down menu that contains links to analytics tools for your repository including: - Pulse: Find information about the work that has been completed and the work that’s in-progress in this project dashboard - Graphs: Graphs provide a more granular view of the repository activity including who contributed to the repository, who forked it, and when they completed the work ### Special Files In the video you learned about a special file called the README.md. Here are a few other special files you can add to your repositories: - CONTRIBUTING.md: The `CONTRIBUTING.md` is used to describe the process for contributing to the repository. A link to the `CONTRIBUTING.md` file is shown anytime someone creates a new issue or pull request. - ISSUE_TEMPLATE.md: The `ISSUE_TEMPLATE.md` is another file you can use to pre-populate the body of an issue. For example, if you always need the same types of information for bug reports, include it in the issue template, and every new issue will be opened with your recommended starter text.
### Using issues This is an issue [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#issue): a place where you can have conversations about bugs in your code, code review, and just about anything else. Issue titles are like email subject lines. They tell your collaborators what the issue is about at a glance. For example, the title of this issue is Getting Started with GitHub.
Using GitHub Issues ## Using GitHub issues Issues are used to discuss ideas, enhancements, tasks, and bugs. They make collaboration easier by: - Providing everyone (even future team members) with the complete story in one place - Allowing you to cross-link to other issues and pull requests [:book:](https://help.github.com/articles/github-glossary/#pull-request) - Creating a single, comprehensive record of how and why you made certain decisions - Allowing you to easily pull the right people and teams into a conversation with @-mentions :tv: [Video: Using issues](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zhj46r5D0nQ)
Managing notifications
## Managing notifications :tv: [Video: Watching, notifications, stars, and explore](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ocQldxF7fMY) Once you've commented on an issue or pull request, you'll start receiving email notifications when there's activity in the thread. ### How to silence or unmute specific conversations 1. Go to the issue or pull request 2. Under _"Notifications"_, click the **Unsubscribe** button on the right to silence notifications or **Subscribe** to unmute them You'll see a short description that explains your current notification status. ### How to customize notifications in Settings 1. Click your profile icon 2. Click **Settings** 3. Click **Notifications** from the menu on the left and [adjust your notification preferences](https://help.github.com/articles/managing-notification-delivery-methods/) ### Repository notification options * **Watch**: You'll receive a notification when a new issue, pull request or comment is posted, and when an issue is closed or a pull request is merged * **Not watching**: You'll no longer receive notifications unless you're @-mentioned * **Ignore**: You'll no longer receive any notifications from the repository ### How to review notifications for the repositories you're watching 1. Click your profile icon 2. Click **Settings** 3. Click **Notification** from the menu on the left 4. Click on the [things you’re watching](https://github.com/watching) link 5. Select the **Watching** tab 6. Click the **Unwatch** button to disable notifications, or **Watch** to enable them

issue_title: [DomCrawler] Inconsistency between children and parents
issue_body:
| Q                | A
| ---------------- | -----
| Bug report?      | yes
| Feature request? | no
| BC Break report? | no
| RFC?             | no
| Symfony version  | all

According to the documentation:

> Get all the child or parent nodes:
>
> $crawler->filter('body')->children();
> $crawler->filter('body > p')->parents();

However, `children()` returns only direct children (not grandchildren...), while `parents()` returns all ancestors (including grandparents...).

Maybe it's more a docs issue than a code issue? Anyway it looks weird to me that methods with similar names have a different behavior.

issue_title: error_bubbling doesn't work properly with inherit_data
[amazoechocontrol] SmartHomeDevice channels not showing on the interface & use mergeApplianceIds to gather the complete device state
issue_body:
Environment: OpenHab3.0 (docker), also tested on OpenHab3.1-Snapshot (macOS).

I was trying to get the temperature from my echo devices and after some time without succeed, I decided to debug the binding to understand it a little better.
After some tests I discover that the temperature channel was added correctly to my things but it was not showed on the interface because the channel-type was not defined on the binding schema. After including the channel-type definitions in the schema the channels were displayed correctly on the interface.
Then I discovered the second issue, after adding some items to my devices I found out that the temperature channel was working correctly on my echo v1 device but not on my echo v4 device. After some research I discovered the problem. When a device from the Alexa api contains the field mergedApplianceIds we should query the state for all the mergedApplianceIds and merge the results instead of just query for the applianceId field.

After I made those changes I was able to use my devices correctly on the OpenHab 3.1 Snapshot.

I hope I have explained the problem clearly, I'm will open a pr in a while that aims to solve this problems so you can review what I changed. 
As always, thanks in advance!

issue_title: Sentry raises `NoMethodError: undefined method 'event_id' for false:FalseClass` on calling Sentry.capture_exception in Rails integration tests
issue_body:
**Describe the bug**

1. A controller is called in a Rails MiniTest integration test.
2. The controller catches an exception and calls `Sentry.capture_exception`.
3. Sentry throws a NoMethodError which causes the controller to fail with a 500 error:

```
Minitest::UnexpectedError:         NoMethodError: undefined method `event_id' for false:FalseClass
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/sentry-ruby-4.1.0/lib/sentry/hub.rb:113:in `capture_event'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/sentry-ruby-4.1.0/lib/sentry/hub.rb:85:in `capture_exception'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/sentry-ruby-4.1.0/lib/sentry-ruby.rb:119:in `capture_exception'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/sentry-ruby-4.1.0/lib/sentry/rack/capture_exceptions.rb:28:in `rescue in block in call'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/sentry-ruby-4.1.0/lib/sentry/rack/capture_exceptions.rb:22:in `block in call'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/sentry-ruby-4.1.0/lib/sentry/hub.rb:50:in `with_scope'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/sentry-ruby-4.1.0/lib/sentry-ruby.rb:103:in `with_scope'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/sentry-ruby-4.1.0/lib/sentry/rack/capture_exceptions.rb:14:in `call'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/railties-5.1.7/lib/rails/engine.rb:522:in `call'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/rack-test-1.1.0/lib/rack/mock_session.rb:29:in `request'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/rack-test-1.1.0/lib/rack/test.rb:266:in `process_request'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/rack-test-1.1.0/lib/rack/test.rb:119:in `request'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/actionpack-5.1.7/lib/action_dispatch/testing/integration.rb:261:in `process'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/actionpack-5.1.7/lib/action_dispatch/testing/integration.rb:28:in `patch'
            /usr/local/bundle/gems/actionpack-5.1.7/lib/action_dispatch/testing/integration.rb:348:in `block (2 levels) in <module:Runner>'
            test/controllers/my_controller_test.rb:63:in `block in <class:MyControllerTest>'
```

Looking at line 113 in sentry/hub.rb, it expects `current_client.capture_event` to either return `nil` or return an object that responds to `event.event_id`. However, as the error indicates, it actually got `false:FalseClass` instead.

Looking at line 85 in sentry/hub.rb and Client.event_from_exception in sentry/client.rb, it looks like event should always be either nil or an instance of Event.

**To Reproduce**

1. Create a controller that calls `Sentry.capture_exception` in a method.
2. Set up a route to the controller method created in step 1.
2. Create a Rails MiniTest integration test that sends a request to the route defined in step 2.

Controller:
```ruby
class MyController < ApplicationController
    def data
      Sentry.capture_exception(RuntimeError.new('Hello, World'))
      render json: { message: 'Hello, World!' }
    end
end
```

Router:
```ruby
Rails.application.routes.draw do
  get 'my/data', to: 'my#data'
end
```

Integration test:
```ruby
require 'test_helper'

class MyControllerTest < ActionDispatch::IntegrationTest
  test 'send request to our controller' do
    get "my/data"
  end
end
```

**Expected behavior**
Sentry should capture the exception without raising any errors.

**Actual behavior**
A NoMethodError is raised.

**Environment**
 - Ruby Version: 2.7.2
 - SDK Version: 4.1.0
 - Rails 5.1.7

**Sentry Config**

```ruby
Sentry.init do |config|
  config.dsn = Rails.application.config.sentry_dsn if Rails.env.production?
end
```

issue_body:

When I try to view any page on https://webpack.js.org/ in Firefox's private browsing mode, I see the site content flash for a split second before it goes black. When I open up the Firefox developer console, I see the following error:

issue_title: [LOWCAR] Test UID for flashed lowcar devices change appear differently within net_handler and dev_handler
issue_body:
When a lowcar device is flashed using the runtime flash script, there is an option to set a test UID instead of a random UID. The test UID is 0x0123456789ABCDEF. However, it seems that when connecting to dev_handler or printing on net_handler_cli shows the UID to be 0x23456789ABCDEF0D. There could be an error on how the UID is being flashed or the way dev_handler could be processing the acknowledgment from the device.

Steps to reproduce:
1) Flash a lowcar device using "runtime flash -t KoalaBear"
2) Start up shared memory and dev_handler
3) Connect flashed lowcar device to dev_handler and observe UID of connected device
4) Print in shared memory to also observe the UID

issue_title: Exceptions when running from folder with space and number in name
issue_body:
### Description

When debugging an application in a folder with a name that includes a space followed by `0<digit>`, a Python traceback is triggered on seemingly every command.

What I think is happening is that pwndbg runs the "info auxv" command in the background every time the user enters a command, and a regular expression in `auxv.py` incorrectly parses the "File name of executable" line, which in this case looks something like this:
```
31   AT_EXECFN            File name of executable        0x7fffffffefde "/home/user/test/x 01/test"
```
There are probably other file- and folder-name patterns that can result in this behavior, too.

### Steps to reproduce

- Make a folder named, for example, "x 01"
- Put any debuggable binary in it (even a basic hello-world works)
- Open it in gdb

issue_title: ZigBeeDiscoveryExtension stops periodic discovery of routers
issue_body:
**Describe the bug**
`ZigBeeDiscoveryExtension` stops the periodic discovery of routers.

**To Reproduce**
- Add a router to a ZigBee network
- Reboot the device/coordinator
- The `ZigBeeDiscoveryExtension` starts discovery
- When the `ZigBeeDiscoveryExtension` updates any information related to the router node, it stops the further periodic discovery if it.

**Relevant Logs**

```

**Additional context**
https://github.com/zsmartsystems/com.zsmartsystems.zigbee/blob/953772b97763c276964bfab584ef6905f29f3442/com.zsmartsystems.zigbee/src/main/java/com/zsmartsystems/zigbee/app/discovery/ZigBeeDiscoveryExtension.java#L235-L241
Whenever the `ZigBeeDiscoveryExtension` receives a `nodeUpdated(..)` for the router, it stops the discovery because the `nodeState` is `UNKNOWN`. This seems to be happening because we don't persist `nodeState` when using `ZigBeeNetworkDataStore`

What do you think the best solution might be here? Do you think we should update the `nodeState` to `ONLINE` when we receive *any* command(in addition to `DeviceAnnounce` and rejoin request) in the extension so that after the first discovery the `nodeState` is always updated to `ONLINE`?

issue_title: Conda-installed CLI 0.10.12 throwing TypeError: 'module' object is not callable
issue_body:
**Describe the bug**
wandb cli is throwing `TypeError: 'module' object is not callable` when running `wandb login` and `wandb sweep sweepfile.yaml`

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Setup Conda environment with python 3.9.1, on Ubuntu 18.04. Install wandb 0.10.12 via conda
2. Run `wandb login` from within the conda environment

**Expected behavior**
CLI wandb should be callable.

**Screenshots**
I got the error below:
```
➜ wanbd login   
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/XX/miniconda3/envs/XXX/bin/wanbd", line 10, in <module>
    sys.exit(cli())
TypeError: 'module' object is not callable
```

**Operating System**
 - OS: Ubuntu 18.04
 - Version 0.10.12

Info on the conda release:
```
➜ conda list wan
# packages in environment at /home/XX/miniconda3/envs/XXX:
#
# Name                    Version                   Build  Channel
wandb                     0.10.12            pyhd3deb0d_0    conda-forge

**Additional info**:

The pip version works as expected.

issue_title: nxos_config cannot execute config-replace on non-9K platforms
issue_body:
##### SUMMARY
The `nxos_config` module claims that config-replace is only supported on the Nexus 9k platforms. While this may have been true in the past, it is false today. Ansible should not be performing platform-specific checks like this as it cripples functionality and artificially couples the automation tool (Ansible) to the managed device's feature set.

##### ISSUE TYPE
- Bug Report

##### COMPONENT NAME
`nxos_config` module

##### ANSIBLE VERSION
```

  config file = /root/cdpc/ansible.cfg

```

##### OS / ENVIRONMENT

CentOS Linux release 7.6.1810 (Core)

##### STEPS TO REPRODUCE
Playbook:
```
$ cat config_replace.yml
- hosts: "n3k"
  tasks:
